EClaudia%20Goldin%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whose%20work%20on%20women's%20rights%2C%20equal%20pay%2C%20and%20the%20motherhood%20penalty%20has%20helped%20spawn%20a%20whole%20field%20of%20economics%20focused%20on%20the%20ways%20that%20pay%20gaps%20develop%20and%20stick%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20lots%20of%20people%20doing%20such%20research%20now%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that%20this%20means%20that%20they'll%20see%20that%20it%20is%20important%20and%20that%20it's%20recognized%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldin%20told%20Insider%20after%20her%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldin%20joins%20an%20esteemed%20group%20of%2093%20laureates%20and%20now%20faces%20one%20of%20the%20questions%20that%20Nobel%20Prize-winning%20economists%20might%20be%20uniquely%20equipped%20to%20answer%3A%20How%20to%20spend%20that%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20perennial%20question%20and%20one%20that%20some%20laureates%20across%20different%20categories%20have%20answered%20by%20splashing%20out%20on%20things%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftheobserver%2F2010%2Foct%2F24%2Fprofile-paul-nurse-dna-genes%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHe%2520used%2520his%2520Nobel%2520prize%2Che%2520has%2520maintained%2520in%2520Oxfordshire.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emotorcycles%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcontent.time.com%2Ftime%2Fspecials%2Fpackages%2Farticle%2F0%2C28804%2C1848817_1848816_1848804%2C00.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehouses%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Others%20have%20put%20it%20towards%20further%20research%2C%20or%20charitable%20causes.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbooks%2F2016%2Foct%2F01%2Fnobel-prize-laureates-money-award%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGuardian%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20laureates%20usually%20get%20their%20prize%20money%20after%20the%20award%20presentation%20in%20Stockholm%3B%20many%20receive%20their%20prizes%20via%20a%20bank%20transfer%2C%20Lars%20Heikenstei