6quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EModigliani%20isn't%20alone%20in%20putting%20his%20winnings%20where%20his%20(research)%20mouth%20is.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nobelprize.org%2Fprizes%2Feconomic-sciences%2F2009%2Fostrom%2Finterview%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EElinor%20Ostrom%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20win%20the%20prize%20for%20her%20research%20on%20common%20resources%2C%20donated%20her%20share%20of%20her%20%241.4%20million%20in%20winnings%20%E2%80%94%20she%20won%20the%20prize%20alongside%20Oliver%20E.%20Williamson%20in%202009%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20Workshop%20in%20Political%20Theory%20and%20Policy%20Analysis%20at%20Indiana%20University%2C%20which%20she%20cofounded%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20according%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3421197%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eobituary%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Proceedings%20of%20the%20National%20Academy%20of%20Sciences%20of%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEsther%20Duflo%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nobelprize.org%2Fprizes%2Feconomic-sciences%2F2019%2Fduflo%2Ffacts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esecond%20woman%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20win%20the%20prize%20for%20her%20work%20on%20poverty%2C%20alongside%20her%20fellow%202019%20winners%20Abhijit%20Banerjee%20(who%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fmoney%2F2019%2F12%2F10%2F786431379%2Fa-q-a-with-esther-duflo-who-wins-nobel-prize-today%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ealso%20her%20husband%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E)%20and%20Michael%20Kremer%2C%20also%20donated%20their%20winnings.%20They%20poured%20about%20%24916%2C000%20into%20the%20Weiss%20Fund%20for%20Research%20in%20Development%20Economics%20at%20Harvard%20University%2C%20which%20helps%20fund%20students%20and%20research%20into%20development%20economics%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bostonglobe.com%2Fbusiness%2F2019%2F12%2F07%2Feconomics-laureates-donate-nobel-prize-money-next-generation-economists%2FdFTJ89hemp4cc3x6uiUTKM%2Fstory.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBoston%20Globe%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Sir%20Angus%20Deaton%2C%20who%20won%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nobelprize.org%2Fprizes%2Feconomic-sciences%2F2015%2Fdeaton%2Ffacts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eprize%20in%202015%20for%20his%20work%20on%20poverty%20and%20inequality%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20the%20Guardian%20that%20he%20had%20%26quot%3Bworked%20on%20trying%20to%20understand%20spending%20and%20saving%20all%20of%20my%20professional%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20had%20learned%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bmakes%20no%20sense%20to%20spend%20a%20once-and-for-all%20windfall.%26quot%3B%20After%20paying%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%26quot%3B%20of%20tax%20on%20his%20winnings%2C%20he%20saved%20the%20rest%20and%20put%20it%20towards%20his%20retirement%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20Thaler%2C%20a%20behavioral%20economist%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%2C%20won%20the%20prize%20for%20his%20work%20on%20how%20humans%20are%2C%20in%20part%2C%20irrational.%20So%20when%20he%20was%20asked%20how%20he'd%20spend%20what%20was%2C%20in%202017%20dollars%2C%20around%20%241.1%20million%20in%20winnings%2C%20Thaler%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2017%2F10%2F09%2Fthe-nobel-prize-winner-for-economics-had-the-perfect-response-to-the-win.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etold%20reporters%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20try%20to%20spend%20it%20as%20irrationally%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20follow-up%20official%20Nobel%20interview%2C%20Thaler%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nobelprize.org%2Fprizes%2Feconomic-sciences%2F2017%2Fthaler%2F159673-richard-thaler-interview-transcript%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eclarified%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20made%20that%20comment%20at%204%3A45%20a.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20have%20the%20money%20yet%20so%20I%20have%20not%20lived%20up%20to%20that%20promise%2C%26quot%3B%20Thaler%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20intend%20to%20throw%20a%20good%20party%20Saturday%20night%20and%20then%20try%20to%20spend%20it%20to%20make%20as%20many%20people%20happy%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nobel-prize-winner-economists-spend-winnings-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700478541000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6553d32122cf74a5739725a2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nobel-prize-winner-economists-spend-winnings-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nobel%20Prize%20winners%20won%20over%20%241%20million%20this%20year.%20Some%20past%20laureates%20have%20used%20their%20money%20on%20everything%20from%20boats%20to%20research.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nobel-prize-winner-economists-spend-winnings-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20boomer%20moved%20from%20San%20Diego%20to%20a%20West%20Virginia%20town%20with%201%2C500%20residents.%20She%20outlined%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20small-town%20life.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shepherdstown%2C%20West%20Virginia%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65567af022cf74a57398d83c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJan%20Pfrimmer%20recently%20moved%20from%20a%20suburb%20of%20San%20Diego%20to%20Shepherdstown%2C%20West%20Virginia.%3Cp%3EGeorgina%20Burrows%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20boomer%20moved%20from%20a%20suburb%20of%20San%20Diego%20to%20Shepherdstown%2C%20West%20Virginia%2C%20which%20has%201%2C500%20residents.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20much%20lower%20and%20it's%20much%20more%20peaceful%2C%20though%20there's%20a%20lot%20less%20going%20on.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20also%20said%20she's%20gotten%20better%20medical%20attention%20in%20West%20Virginia.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJan%20Pfrimmer%2C%2072%2C%20has%20lived%20all%20over%20the%20place.%20She%20traveled%20the%20US%20as%20a%20flying%20trapeze%20artist%2C%20lived%20in%20Mexico%20City%20for%20a%20year%2C%20dealt%20cards%20in%20Reno%20and%20Tahoe%2C%20and%20lived%20in%20a%20city%20just%20outside%20of%20San%20Diego%20for%20a%20decade%20where%20she%20worked%20as%20an%20accountant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPfrimmer%2C%20who%20has%20spent%20the%20majority%20of%20her%20life%20in%20California%2C%20was%20ready%20for%20another%20move.%20This%20time%2C%20to%20a%20small%20town%20of%201%2C500%20residents%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-to-a-small-town-in-west-virginia-to-escape-big-city-life-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWest%20Virginia%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20Shepherdstown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPfrimmer%20said%20there%20was%20little%20left%20for%20her%20in%20California%2C%20as%20her%20husband%20died%2010%20years%20ago%20and%20most%20of%20her%20family%20moved%20out%20of%20state.%20She%20moved%20to%20West%20Virginia%20in%20May%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20her%20family%20and%20to%20get%20away%20from%20the%20rather%20pricey%20hustle%20and%20bustle%20of%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20cool%20to%20be%20able%20to%20slow%20down%20and%20really%20enjoy%20the%20stuff%20that%20money%20can't%20buy%20like%20the%20trees%20turning%20colors%2C%20or%20the%20leaves%20and%20bird%20songs%2C%26quot%3B%20Pfrimmer%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20stress%20has%20gone%20out%20of%20my%20life%2C%20and%20I%20think%20everybody%20in%20California%20pretty%20much%20lives%20with%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20stress%20since%20it's%20fast-paced.%20There's%20no%20getting%20around%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWest%20Virginia%20is%20not%20a%20particularly%20popular%20destination%20for%20former%20Californians.%20Of%20the%20approximately%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-texas-moving-arizona-florida-expensive-housing-costs-washington-nevada-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E818%2C000%20former%20Californians%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20moved%20to%20other%20states%20from%202021%20to%202022%2C%20just%20879%20moved%20to%20West%20Virginia.%20On%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20just%2042%20former%20West%20Virginians%20moved%20to%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Californians%20have%20been%20leaving%20for%20states%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-from-california-to-texas-pros-cons-silicon-valley-boerne-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETexas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-from-california-to-tennessee-pros-cons-san-diego-murfreesboro-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETennessee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-from-california-to-kentucky-pros-cons-san-diego-paducah-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKentucky%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20search%20of%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20better%20weather%2C%20and%20a%20slower%20pace%20of%20life.%20Still%2C%20some%20residents%20in%20areas%20where%20many%20out-of-staters%20are%20moving%20have%20been%20priced%20out%20and%20thus%20have%20to%20look%20to%20other%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'There's%20nothing%20left%20for%20me%20there'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPfrimmer%20said%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-texas-california-florida-new-york-housing-expensive-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edidn't%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20California%3C%2Fa%3E%20anymore%2C%20but%20she%20wasn't%20quite%20sure%20what%20her%20next%20move%20would%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20very%20expensive%20to%20live%20there%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20people%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Pfrimmer%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20they%20have%20to%20sometimes%20choose%20between%20paying%20their%20electric%20bill%20and%20getting%20food.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20for%20years%20she's%20contemplated%20leaving%20because%20of%20wildfires%2C%20especially%20as%20more%20and%20more%20home%20insurers%20are%20pulling%20out%20of%20her%20area%20of%20California.%20Her%20commute%20at%20her%20accounting%20job%2C%20she%20said%2C%20was%20sometimes%20an%20hour%20or%20two%20each%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUntil%20you've%20had%20a%20fire%20come%20down%20into%20almost%20your%20backyard%2C%20you%20have%20no%20idea%20how%20scary%20that%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Pfrimmer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20though%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-from-florida-to-california-pros-cons-los-angeles-orlando-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20weather%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20nature%20kept%20her%20glued%20to%20California.%20She%20lived%2020%20minutes%20away%20from%20the%20coast%2C%20and%20she%20said%20within%20two%20hours%2C%20she%20could%20drive%20to%20a%20desert%20or%20snow.%20But%20this%20alone%20wasn't%20enough%20to%20stop%20her%20from%20moving%2C%20especially%20as%20she%20came%20to%20view%20the%20people%20in%20California%20as%20not%20very%20friendly%20and%20with%20different%20approaches%20to%20life%20than%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20just%20striving%20for%20more%20money%2C%20more%20of%20this%2C%20more%20of%20that%2C%20and%20it%20kind%20of%20gets%20out%20there%20into%20the%20universe%2C%20at%20least%20in%20California%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20finding%20in%20West%20Virginia%20it's%20just%20everybody's%20been%20wonderful%2C%20and%20it's%20slower%2C%20and%20I%20can%20breathe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeighing%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPfrimmer's%20move%20from%20California%20to%20West%20Virginia%20was%20so%20smooth%20she%20suspected%20it%20may%20be%20%26quot%3Bpreordained.%26quot%3B%20The%20moving%20team%20was%20thorough%2C%20she%20found%20a%20home%20that%20fit%20her%20wants%2C%20and%20she%20rather%20quickly%20acclimated%20to%20the%20new%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20much%20lower%20in%20Shepherdstown%2C%20from%20taxes%20to%20utility%20bills.%20She%20sold%20her%201%2C200-square-foot%20California%20home%20for%20%24630%2C000%20that%20she%20bought%20for%20%24151%2C000.%20She%20said%20it%20later%20sold%20for%20nearly%20%24900%2C000%20a%20month%20and%20a%20half%20later.%20In%20West%20Virginia%2C%20she%20bought%20a%201%2C700-square-foot%20townhouse%20for%20%24285%2C000%2C%20and%20she%20installed%20a%20new%20roof%20for%20only%20%245%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20median%20listing%20price%20for%20a%20home%20in%20Shepherdstown%20is%20%24572%2C500%2C%20whereas%20it's%20%24747%2C400%20in%20Santee%2C%20the%20San%20Diego%20suburb%20where%20she%20previously%20lived%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.realtor.com%2Frealestateandhomes-search%2FSantee_CA%2Foverview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%20to%20Realtor.com%20estimates%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20car%20insurance%2C%20registration%20costs%2C%20and%20taxes%20are%20also%20considerably%20less.%20She%20estimates%20she's%20paying%20around%20a%20quarter%20of%20what%20she%20paid%20in%20California%20for%20monthly%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20likes%20how%20Shepherdstown%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shepherd.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euniversity%20town%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20younger%2C%20more%20liberal%20students.%20Still%2C%20t