C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2020%2F11%2F03%2Fus%2Felections%2Fexit-polls-president.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eone-quarter%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20all%20LGBTQ%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%20view%20Johnson%2C%20I%20recently%20spoke%20with%20Charles%20Moran%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Log%20Cabin%20Republicans.%20Founded%20in%201977%2C%20Log%20Cabin%20is%20the%20country's%20leading%20conservative%20LGBTQ%20organization%2C%20and%20claims%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20members%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20an%20interview%20at%20the%20organization's%20headquarters%20in%20a%20Capitol%20Hill%20townhouse%2C%20Moran%20spoke%20about%20the%20conversations%20he's%20had%20with%20Johnson's%20staff%2C%20his%20perspective%20on%20Johnson's%20views%2C%20and%20why%20he's%20willing%20to%20offer%20the%20new%20speaker%20the%20%26quot%3Bbenefit%20of%20the%20doubt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20aware%20were%20you%20of%20Mike%20Johnson%20before%20he%20became%20speaker%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20no%20idea%20who%20he%20was%20before%20becoming%20Speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObviously%2C%20I%20think%20everybody%20was%20just%20trying%20to%20get%20up%20to%20speed%20the%20minute%20his%20name%20was%20being%20floated.%20We%20did%20Steve%20Scalise%2C%20and%20then%20we%20did%20Tom%20Emmer%2C%20and%20then%E2%80%A6%20was%20Johnson%20the%20next%20one%3F%20Was%20there%20any%20other%20name%20in%20there%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou're%20forgetting%20Jim%20Jordan.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOh%2C%20Jim%20Jordan.%20Yeah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20mean%2C%20I%20think%20everybody%20was%20just%20kind%20of%20riding%20that%20wave.%20I%20have%20personal%20opinions%20on%20all%20of%20these%20people%2C%20we%20as%20Log%20Cabin%20have%20engaged%20at%20some%20level%20with%20all%20of%20those%20people%20%E2%80%94%20until%20we%20got%20to%20Mike%20Johnson.%20He's%20somebody%20we%20just%20had%20not%20engaged%20with%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20have%20strong%20relationships%20with%20legislators%20in%20Louisiana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20your%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FLogCabinGOP%2Fstatus%2F1717374578404569111%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3Einitial%20statement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20on%20Johnson's%20election%20as%20speaker%2C%20you%20wrote%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bimperative%20that%20he%20work%20to%20implement%20an%20agenda%20that%20advances%20the%20interests%20of%20all%20Americans.%26quot%3B%20That%20portion%20was%20in%20bold.%20What%20did%20you%20mean%20by%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20he's%20the%20Speaker%20of%20the%20House%2C%20he%20has%20to%20speak%20for%20not%20only%20his%20district%2C%20but%20also%20the%20Republican%20Conference%20and%20the%20entire%20House%20of%20Representatives.%20When%20you're%20looking%20at%20carrots%20and%20sticks%2C%20I%20want%20to%20always%20start%20with%20a%20carrot%2C%20I%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20give%20folks%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20they're%20in%20a%20different%20type%20of%20leadership%20role%20where%20they%20have%20a%20much%20larger%20constituency%20to%20take%20into%20consideration%2C%20what%20I%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20is%20provide%20them%20with%20the%20ammunition%20and%20the%20backup%20to%20show%20that%20a%20vast%20majority%20of%20not%20just%20Americans%2C%20but%20Republicans%20in%20this%20country%2C%20support%20equality%20and%20equal%20access%20for%20the%20LGBT%20community%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Ls%2C%20the%20Gs%2C%20the%20Bs%2C%20and%20the%20Ts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20that%20was%20the%20intended%20purpose%20of%20the%20bold%2C%20was%20to%20remind%20the%20new%20speaker%20and%20his%20team%20of%20his%20new%20expanded%20constituency%20that%20may%20not%20be%20as%20loud%20and%20as%20vocal%20in%20his%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20you%20mean%20by%20%26quot%3Bammunition%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFacts%2C%20figures%2C%20personal%20stories%2C%20and%20narratives.%20Those%20are%20all%20things%20that%20impact%20a%20legislator.%20Research%20has%20shown%20that%20if%20you%20know%20somebody%20who's%20LGBT%20%E2%80%94%20an%20L%2C%20a%20G%2C%20a%20B%2C%20or%20a%20T%20%E2%80%94%20you%20have%20a%20much%20higher%20chance%20of%20being%20supportive%20of%20those%20equality%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20not%20to%20predetermine%20or%20predispose%20the%20speaker%2C%20I%20just%20don't%20know%20how%20many%20gay%20people%20he%20knows.%20His%20district%20is%20very%20deeply%20red%2C%20it's%20socially%20very%20conservative.%20My%20family's%20from%20Louisiana%2C%20so%20I%20know%20the%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20not%20to%20predispose%20people%20for%20being%20hateful%2C%20who%20are%20from%20the%20South.%20They're%20some%20of%20the%20nicest%2C%20kindest%20people.%20But%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20that%20type%20of%20diversity%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20personal%20stories%2C%20or%20personal%20experiences%2C%20you%20may%20not%20know%20how%20important%20it%20is%20to%20take%20those%20into%20consideration%20when%20you're%20voting%20on%20issues%2C%20and%20when%20you're%20expounding%20on%20public%20policy%20positions.%20We%20want%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20the%20leadership%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20you%20all%20reached%20out%20to%20his%20team%20yet%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20and%20they%20responded%20within%20four%20hours%20to%20set%20up%20a%20meeting%20with%20senior%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHas%20that%20meeting%20occurred%3F%20How%20was%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes.%20It%20was%20a%20week%20and%20a%20half%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVery%20supportive%2C%20it%20was%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20not%20gonna%20tell%20you%20who%20it%20was%2C%20but%20it%20was%20with%20senior%20folks%20in%20his%20office.%20I%20used%20Congresswoman%20Kat%20Cammack%20as%20a%20go-between%2C%20she%20personally%20has%20a%20good%20relationship%20with%20the%20speaker.%20They%20put%20us%20in%20touch%20with%20Speaker%20Johnson's%20office%2C%20and%20literally%2C%20once%20I%20sent%20them%20the%20email%2C%20they%20responded%20and%20set%20up%20a%20meeting%2C%20on%20a%20weekend%2C%20the%20next%20day.%20That's%20fast%20in%20this%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20explained%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20talk%20to%20them%20about%2C%20and%20it's%20some%20of%20the%20things%20we're%20talking%20about%20now%2C%20like%3A%20how%20are%20we%20going%20to%20discuss%20this%3F%20Where's%20the%20speaker%20on%20some%20of%20these%20issues%3F%20Some%20things%20they%20had%20answers%20to%2C%20some%20things%20they%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20appreciate%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20have%20allies%20on%20the%20Hill%20who%20are%20willing%20to%20help%2C%20and%20how%20fast%20the%20speaker's%20team%20engaged%20with%20us.%20I%20mean%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20times%20when%20you%20send%20these%20emails%20and%20it%20goes%20into%20the%20ether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECould%20you%20get%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20specific%20about%20what%20you%20discussed%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20thing%20that%20came%20out%20of%20it%20was%20just%20kind%20of%20a%20framework%20on%20how%20the%20speaker%20views%20things%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20mean%2C%20I%20did%20not%20walk%20in%20with%20a%20list%20of%2010%20questions%20on%2C%20%3Cem%3EHow%20does%20he%20feel%20about%20X%3F%20Where's%20he%20going%20to%20be%20on%20Y%3F%20What%20is%20he%20going%20to%20vote%20on%20Z%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20Obviously%2C%20we%20know%20where%20his%20past%20has%20been.%20His%20writings%2C%20his%20voting%20record%20on%20some%20things%2C%20some%20of%20it's%20more%20troubling%20than%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20moving%20forward%20as%20speaker%2C%20again%2C%20we%20want%20to%20give%20him%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt%2C%20because%20now%20he's%20got%20a%20much%20larger%20constituency%2C%20and%20quite%20honestly%2C%20really%20big%20issues.%20I%20mean%2C%20averting%20a%20government%20shutdown%20was%20a%20really%20big%20test%2C%20trying%20to%20get%20some%20of%20these%20other%20bills%20passed%20is%20a%20really%20big%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20things%20that%20we%20came%20away%20with%20from%20that%20conversation%20was%20one%2C%20the%20speaker%20is%20not%20looking%20to%20re-litigate%20settled%20law.%20So%20I%20took%20that%20as%2C%20you%20know%2C%20things%20like%20Obergefell%2C%20things%20like%20Respect%20for%20Marriage%2C%20Don't%20Ask%2C%20Don't%20Tell%2C%20you%20know%2C%20any%20of%20the%20stuff%20that%20has%20been%20voted%20on%20or%20just%20settled%20already.%20He's%20not%20necessarily%20looking%20to%20deal%20with%20that%2C%20so%20that's%20very%20helpful%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20operating%20principle%20that%20they're%20going%20with%20is%20building%20consensus.%20He%20has%20a%20mandate%20and%20a%20job%20as%20the%20speaker%20to%20build%20consensus%20to%20get%20bills%20passed%2C%20not%20just%20these%20funding%20bills%2C%20but%20other%20issues%20around%20public%20policy.%20So%20things%20that%20do%20not%20have%20that%20consensus%20are%20things%20that%20he's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20pushing%2C%20which%20gives%20me%20cautious%20optimism%20that%20he's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20picking%20up%20any%20kind%20of%20hot-button%2C%20hardline%20social%20issues%20and%20trying%20to%20push%20in%20opposition%20to%20LGBT%20equality%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBefore%20Mike%20Johnson%2C%20Tom%20Emmer%20was%20the%20party's%20nominee%20for%20speaker%20%E2%80%94%20for%20a%20few%20hours.%20But%20he%20was%20forced%20to%20withdraw%20his%20candidacy%20in%20part%20due%20to%20concerns%20about%20his%20support%20for%20the%20Respect%20for%20Marriage%20Act.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMarjorie%20Taylor%20Greene%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FRepMTG%2Fstatus%2F1716894270097883637%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3Esaid%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20she%20voted%20against%20him%20in%20part%20because%20he%20voted%20for%20the%20%26quot%3BDemocrat%20gay%20marriage%20bill.%26quot%3B%20There%20was%20also%20Rick%20Allen%20from%20Georgia%2C%20who%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailybeast.com%2Frepublicans-gasped-during-reps-confrontation-with-tom-emmer-report%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3Ereportedly%20told%20him%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20during%20a%20closed-door%20caucus%20meeting%2C%20regarding%20his%20vote%20for%20that%20bill%2C%20that%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20get%20right%20with%20Jesus.%26quot%3B%20What%20does%20that%20episode%20say%20to%20you%20about%20the%20state%20of%20the%20party%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20the%20last%20thing%20that%20I'd%20do%20is%20use%20statements%20from%20two%20members%20from%20rural%20Georgia%20as%20a%20blanket%20filter%20through%20which%20to%20view%20all%20members%20of%20the%20House%20Republican%20Conference%2C%20especially%20people%20like%20Marjorie%20Taylor%20Greene.%20They%20don't%20represent%20the%20entire%20conference.%20If%20they%20want%20to%20criticize%20people%20like%20Tom%20Emmer%20like%20that%2C%20that's%20their%20prerogative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOkay%2C%20so%20a%20couple%20members%20didn't%20like%20the%20fact%20that%20Emmer%20voted%20for%20the%20Respect%20for%20Marriage%20Act.%20Guess%20what%3F%2047%20Republicans%2C%20on%20the%20first%20round%2C%20voted%20for%20it.%20Yeah%2C%20there%20are%20members%20of%20the%20House%20conference%20that%20don't%20support%20gay%20marriage%2C%20guess%20what%3F%20That%20bill%20passed%20the%20House%2C%20and%20it%20passed%20the%20Senate%20only%20because%20Republicans%20voted%20for%20it.%20Which%20also%20doesn't%20get%20the%20type%20of%20credit%20it%20needs%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20too%20bad%2C%20so%20sad%2C%20the%20House%20and%20the%20Senate%20reflected%20the%20will%20of%20the%20American%20people%2C%20and%20then%20Joe%20Biden%20signed%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20you're%20out%20of%20step%2C%20you're%20out%20of%20line%2C%20Marjorie%2C%20if%20you've%20got%20a%20problem%20with%20gay%20marriage.%20I've%20had%20Marjorie%20Taylor%20Greene%20sit%20in%20this%20room%2C%20and%20we've%20had%20conversations%20about%20areas%20of%20things%20that%20we%20agree%20on%2C%20and%20things%20we%20don't.%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20shit%20all%20over%20her%20because%20I%20disagree%20with%20her%20on%20this.%20I'm%20sure%20there's%20plenty%20of%20other%20reasons%20why%20she%20didn't%20support%20Tom%20Emmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20government%20funding%20bill%20that%20Johnson's%20conference%20has%20proposed%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F11%2F13%2Ftrump-hiv-republicans-prep-00126468%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3Ewould%20slash%20the%20budget%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20of%20the%20Ending%20the%20HIV%20Epidemic%20in%20the%20US%20Initiative.%20To%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20credit%2C%20this%20is%20a%20program%20that%20his%20administration%20put%20a%20lot%20of%20muscle%20behind.%20Do%20those%20proposed%20cuts%20concern%20you%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbsolutely.%20Republicans%20have%20been%20on%20record%20for%20decades%20supporting%20HIV-AIDS%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20this%20is%20an%20absolute%20backslide%2C%20and%20a%20backstab.%20And%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20byproduct%20of%20what%20we%20saw%20over%20the%20summer%20with%20Dylan%20Mulvaney%20and%20Bud%20Light%2C%20Target%20and%20tuck-friendly%20swimsuits%2C%20and%20I%20think%20anything%20LGBT%20policy-related%20right%20now%20is%20subject%20to%20a%20heightened%20level%20of%20scrutiny%20because%20of%20the%20pendulum%20swing%20%E2%80%94%20it%20moved%20so%20far%20to%20the%20left%2C%20and%20now%20the%20conversation%20is%20sliding%20so%20far%20to%20the%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20very%20serious%20concern.%20Republicans%20need%20to%20be%20on%20the%20record%2C%20not%20because%20it%20looks%20good%2C%20but%20because%20it's%20good%20public%20policy%2C%20and%20it's%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20anybody%20who%20claims%20to%20be%20a%20Trump%20supporter%20votes%20against%20this%2C%20I'm%20just%20gonna%20say%2C%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20vote%20against%20this%2C%20you're%20voting%20against%20President%20Trump's%20marquee%20health%20policy%20initiative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoing%20back%20to%20Johnson%2C%20you've%20alluded%20to%20his%20past.%20I%20wanted%20to%20throw%20out%20a%20few%20specific%20things%20and%20see%20what%20you%20think%20about%20them.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%202003%2C%20he%20argued%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20criminalization%20of%20gay%20sex.%20He%20also%20said%20in%202008%20that%20%26quot%3Brampant%20homosexual%20behavior%26quot%3B%20contributed%20to%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Roman%20Empire.%20He%20gave%20legal%20advice%20to%20a%20group%20that%20promoted%20conversion%20therapy.%20What%20do%20you%20make%20of%20that%20past%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20mean%2C%20these%20are%20all%20issues%2C%20statements%2C%20things%20that%20are%20out%20of%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20during%20that%20time%2C%20President%20Obama%20or%20then-Vice%20President%20Biden%20were%20supportive%20of%20LGBT%20equality.%20I%20don't%20think%20that%20Hillary%20Clinton%20was%20at%20that%20time%20either.%20It's%20not%20an%20excuse%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20denial.%20I%20just%20think%20it's%20entertaining%20that%20the%20mainstream%20media%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20Democrats%20want%20to%20sit%20here%20and%20like%2C%20go%20back%20to%20the%20early%202000s%20on%20these%20things%2C%20and%20they%20do%20it%20with%20Republicans%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20it%20with%20Democrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20weren't%20arguing%20to%20keep%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oyez.org%2Fcases%2F2002%2F02-102%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ELawrence%20v.%20Texas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20in%20place%2C%20though.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20but%20Hillary%20Clinton%2C%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20and%20Barack%20Obama%20were%20going%20on%20national%20television%20and%20discussing%20their%20opposition%20to%20same-sex%20marriage%2C%20and%20were%20supporting%20the%20Defense%20of%20Marriage%20Act.%20They%20were%20supporting%20Don't%20Ask%2C%20Don't%20Tell.%20This%20organization%2C%20Log%20Cabin%2C%20we're%20the%20only%20national%20LGBT%20organization%20that%20actually%20had%20a%20successful%20federal%20lawsuit%20challenging%20Don't%20Ask%2C%20Don't%20Tell.%20Our%20organization%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2010%2F10%2F13%2Fus%2F13military.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egoing%20up%20against%3C%2Fa%3E%20%5Bthen-Attorney%20General%5D%20Eric%20Holder.%20Eric%20Holder%20and%20Barack%20Obama%20were%20arguing%20to%20keep%20DADT%20in%20place.%20But%20funny%20that's%20not%20really%20mentioned%20or%20brought%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20%5Bstatements%20from%20Johnson%5D%20are%20out%20of%20sync%20with%20where%20the%20Republican%20Party%20is%2C%20it's%20out%20of%20sync%20with%20where%20the%20country%20is%2C%20and%20it%20may%20have%20been%20more%20in%20sync%20back%20in%202003%2C%20and%202004%2C%20but%20today%2C%20it's%20totally%20out%20of%20sync.%20Democrats%20have%20been%20given%20the%20opportunity%20to%20grow%20and%20develop%20their%20opinions%2C%20and%20I%20would%20expect%20everybody%20to%20give%20Republicans%20the%20opportunity%20to%20do%20so%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20mean%2C%20I%20know%20that%20he%20introduced%20a%20version%20of%20the%20Florida%20parental%20rights%20bill%20on%20the%20federal%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20going%20to%20ask%20you%20about%20that.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20haven't%20looked%20specifically%20at%20the%20text%20of%20that%20bill%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20remember%20what%20the%20grade%20and%20age%20level%20was%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETen%20years%20old.%20It%20was%20the%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-mike-johnson-republican-speaker-house-louisiana-2023-10%23last-year-he-introduced-a-bill-similar-to-floridas-dont-say-gay-law-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3BStop%20the%20Sexualization%20of%20Children%20Act%20of%202022.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20It%20would%20prohibit%20federal%20funds%20from%20being%20used%20to%20promote%20%26quot%3Bany%20sexually-oriented%20program%2C%20event%2C%20or%20literature%20for%20children%20under%20the%20age%20of%2010.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECritics%20say%20that%20the%20definition%20of%20sexually-oriented%20material%20includes%20%26quot%3Bany%20topic%20involving%20gender%20identity%2C%20gender%20dysphoria%2C%20transgenderism%2C%20sexual%20orientation%2C%20or%20related%20subjects.%26quot%3B%20Folks%20like%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Campaign%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrc.org%2Fpress-releases%2Fhuman-rights-campaign-denounces-federal-bill-that-would-impose-sweeping-dont-say-gay-or-trans-restrictions-nationally%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3Esay%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20that%20this%20is%20an%20effort%20to%20%26quot%3Bstigmatize%20and%20marginalize%26quot%3B%20the%20LGBTQ%20community.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20age%2010%20is%20what%20%E2%80%94%20third%20or%20fourth%20grade%3F%20Vast%20numbers%20of%20Americans%2C%20according%20to%20public%20polling%2C%20agree%20with%20Speaker%20Johnson's%20position%20on%20that.%20%3Cem%3E%5BEditor's%20note%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpro.morningconsult.com%2Finstant-intel%2Fflorida-desantis-dont-say-gay-bill-survey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EPolling%20from%202022%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20found%20that%20a%20slim%2051%25%20majority%20supported%20Florida's%20Parental%20Rights%20in%20Education%20Law%2C%20known%20to%20critics%20as%20%26quot%3BDon't%20Say%20Gay.%26quot%3B%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20HRC%20can%20sit%20there%20and%20say%20that%20this%20is%20discriminatory.%20That's%20just%20out%20of%20line%2C%20and%20out%20of%20sync.%20Log%20Cabin%20disagrees%20with%20that.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20first%20version%20of%20the%20Florida%20parental%20rights%20bill%2C%20Log%20Cabin%20had%20a%20hand%20in%20helping%20craft%20that.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20we%20supported%20it.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20age%20was%20taken%20up%20to%2018.%20We%20opposed%20it%2C%20because%20that%20is%20out%20of%20sync.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnything%20that%20%5BHRC%5D%20opposes%2C%20or%20anything%20that%20tries%20to%20put%20some%20sort%20of%20norm%20or%20decency%20into%20this%2C%20they're%20just%20going%20to%20call%20it%20transphobic%20and%20homophobic.%20That's%20what%20they%20do.%20It's%20not%20based%20in%20any%20kind%20of%20reality%2C%20and%20it's%20certainly%20not%20based%20in%20anything%20where%20the%20public%20currently%20is.%20And%20this%20is%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20why%20we're%20seeing%20such%20extreme%20backlash%20to%20LGBT%20rights.%20It's%20exactly%20because%20of%20things%20like%20what%20HRC%20is%20saying.%20And%20it's%20dangerous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20described%20Johnson's%20views%20in%202003%20as%20being%20out%20of%20sync.%20Now%20here%20he%20is%2C%20last%20year%2C%20introducing%20this%20bill.%20Critics%20see%20a%20broader%20animus%20behind%20this.%20They%20say%20yes%2C%20maybe%20the%20text%20of%20the%20legislation%20is%20reasonable%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20homophobic%20intent%20there%2C%20there's%20an%20anti-LGBTQ%20animus%20behind%20it.%20Do%20you%20think%20that's%20the%20case%20at%20all%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20that%20he's%20really%20passionate%20around%20some%20of%20these%20socially%20conservative%20issues.%20You%20know%2C%20it%20tracks%20with%20where%20he%20is%20on%20abortion.%20I'm%20not%20surprised%20it%20tracks%20with%20where%20he%20is%20on%20gay%20marriage%2C%20it%20tracks%20with%20where%20he%20is%20on%20LGBT%20acceptance%20issues%20in%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20I've%20never%20met%20the%20man%20and%20I%20haven't%20had%20the%20conversation%20of%2C%20do%20you%20have%20anybody%20in%20either%20your%20family%2C%20or%20in%20your%20close%20network%20of%20friends%2C%20or%20even%20your%20extended%20network%20of%20friends%2C%20who's%20gay%3F%20Like%2C%20do%20you%20know%20anyone%3F%20Have%20you%20ever%20had%20a%20gay%20staff%20member%3F%20Have%20you%20actually%20been%20in%20a%20trusted%2C%20safe%20space%20where%20you%20can%20actually%20ask%20some%20of%20these%20questions%20and%20quote-unquote%2C%20get%20to%20know%20a%20gay%2C%20and%20have%20it%20done%20from%20a%20positive%2C%20not%20accusatory%20standpoint%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20right%20now%2C%20I%20actually%20don't%20really%20care%20what%20his%20personal%20opinion%20is%20on%20these%20things.%20I%20need%20to%20know%20that%20as%20the%20Speaker%20of%20the%20House%2C%20he's%20going%20to%20lead%20from%20that%20place%20of%20consensus%20building%2C%20and%20not%20looking%20to%20overturn%20or%20repeal%20things%20that%20have%20already%20been%20voted%20on%2C%20or%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20already%20decided.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20office%20has%20committed%20to%20me%20that%20that's%20his%20framework%20for%20viewing%20things%20moving%20forward.%20So%20as%20long%20as%20he%20sticks%20to%20that%2C%20I'm%20okay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20it's%20not%20maybe%20as%20%26quot%3Bideal%26quot%3B%20as%20we%20wanted%2C%20but%20we've%20got%20to%20see%20if%20this%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20ori