ay%20be%20a%20gold%20mine.%20Being%20able%20to%20understand%20customers'%20genuine%20thoughts%2C%20feelings%2C%20and%20personalities%20would%20make%20it%20a%20lot%20easier%20for%20companies%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacial-detection-technology-alfi-tablets-uber-test-privacy-gdpr-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esell%20their%20products%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Imagine%20you're%20browsing%20on%20a%20shopping%20app%20and%20you%20don't%20like%20what%20you're%20seeing.%20With%20EAI%2C%20the%20app%20could%20tell%20in%20an%20instant%20and%20quickly%20serve%20up%20the%20kind%20of%20content%20that%20it%20thought%20would%20make%20you%20feel%20good%20%E2%80%94%20and%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20buy.%20Some%20businesses%20are%20already%20using%20the%20tech%20to%20make%20smart%20toys%2C%20robotics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdriver-monitoring-system-requirement-seeing-machines-tobii-jungo-cipia-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evehicles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatbot-pi-offers-personal-assistant-advice-how-it-works-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eempathetic%20AI%20chatbots%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Beyond%20commercial%20uses%2C%20EAI%20could%20help%20companies%20in%20the%20workplace%3A%20Knowing%20the%20emotional%20state%20of%20a%20prospective%20or%20current%20employee%20can%20help%20companies%20make%20decisions%20that%20improve%20productivity%20and%20keep%20things%20humming%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20a%20catch%3A%20It's%20not%20clear%20that%20EAI%20even%20works.%20The%20science%20behind%20the%20tech%20is%20disputed%20by%20experts%20in%20the%20field%2C%20and%20some%20critics%20say%20that%20understanding%20how%20we%20feel%20by%20examining%20our%20facial%20expressions%20isn't%20possible.%20But%20that%20isn't%20stopping%20companies%20from%20using%20EAI%20to%20spy%20on%20their%20employees%2C%20determine%20how%20they%20feel%2C%20and%20identify%20who%20should%20be%20hired%20and%20who%20should%20be%20fired.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-radically-reshape-job-market-global-economy-employee-labor-innovation-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20is%20poised%20to%20influence%20all%20parts%20of%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20this%20may%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20insidious.%20Without%20us%20even%20realizing%2C%20our%20bosses%20could%20be%20guessing%20our%20private%20emotions%20%E2%80%94%20and%20using%20them%20against%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20it%20works%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20versions%20of%20emotion%20AI%20have%20been%20in%20development%20since%20the%20late%201990s%2C%20the%20industry%20has%20taken%20off%20in%20recent%20years%20as%20the%20underlying%20tech%20that%20powers%20the%20AI%20has%20become%20more%20sophisticated%20and%20interest%20in%20the%20field%20has%20increased.%20Today%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20data%20that%20EAI%20can%20be%20trained%20on%20is%20overwhelming.%20Companies%20use%20the%20tech%20to%20measure%20things%20including%20breathing%2C%20heart%20rate%2C%20perspiration%2C%20changes%20in%20the%20electrical%20conductance%20of%20our%20skin%2C%20and%20body%20posture.%20That%20data%20is%20then%20used%20for%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20applications%2C%20such%20as%20detecting%20when%20someone%20may%20be%20lying%20about%20insurance%20claims%2C%20helping%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ellipsishealth.com%2Fresearch%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediagnose%20depression%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fc0b03d1d-f72f-48a8-b342-b4a926109452%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etracking%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20students%20are%20responding%20to%20a%20teacher%20during%20online%20learning.%20Some%20versions%20of%20EAI%20are%20focused%20on%20verbal%20cues%2C%20tracking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-salesforce-cogito-companion-detects-depression-in-voice-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etiny%20conversation%20pauses%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20tonal%20shifts.%20Others%20take%20into%20account%20changes%20in%20pupil%20dilation%20and%20gaze.%20There%20are%20also%20models%20that%20can%20read%20your%20emails%2C%20texts%2C%20or%20other%20messages%2C%20and%20generate%20in-depth%20reports%20on%20what%20underlying%20emotions%20you%20may%20be%20unconsciously%20expressing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGabi%20Zijderveld%2C%20the%20chief%20marketing%20officer%20of%20Smart%20Eye%2C%20an%20EAI%20company%20that%20claims%20its%20tech%20%26quot%3Bunderstands%2C%20supports%2C%20and%20predicts%20human%20behavior%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20firm%20had%20amassed%20vast%20amounts%20of%20emotion-based%20data%20by%20analyzing%20over%2014.5%20million%20videos%20of%20facial%20expressions%20it%20made%20with%20voluntary%20participants.%20She%20described%20its%20AI%20as%20%26quot%3Bbasically%20looking%20at%20the%20human%2C%20looking%20at%20facial-expression%20analysis%2C%20people's%20movement%2C%20people's%20nonverbal%20cues%20%E2%80%94%20as%20we%20like%20to%20say%20%E2%80%94%20to%20understand%20what%20their%20emotional%20and%2C%20perhaps%2C%20cognitive%20state%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20system%20from%20Google%20Vision%2C%20performing%20Facial%20Recognition%20and%20emotion%20analysis%20on%20a%20photograph%20of%20a%20man%2C%20with%20facial%20features%20identified%20and%20facial%20bounding%20boxes%20present%2C%20San%20Ramon%2C%20California%2C%20November%2022%2C%202019.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65196bf45e3a3c00199a1fcc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223069%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20example%20of%20emotion%20AI%20facial%20analysis.%20EAI%20companies%20claim%20their%20tech%20can%20tell%20what%20someone%20is%20feeling.%3Cp%3ESmith%20Collection%2FGado%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESmart%20Eye%20uses%20this%20tech%20for%20things%20such%20as%20driver-monitoring%20systems%20that%20detect%20driver%20fatigue%20using%20a%20mixture%20of%20facial%20analysis%20and%20eye%20tracking.%20It%20also%20provides%20analytics%20for%20advertising%20and%20entertainment%20companies.%20In%20these%20cases%2C%20paid%20participants%20watch%20online%20videos%2C%20and%20their%20facial%20expressions%20are%20analyzed%20by%20EAI%20technology%20to%20determine%20whether%20a%20joke%20in%20an%20ad%20was%20funny%20or%20whether%20a%20particular%20moment%20in%20a%20movie%20trailer%20elicited%20the%20emotional%20response%20it%20was%20meant%20to.%20(Zijderveld%20emphasized%20that%20participation%20in%20these%20test%20groups%20was%20always%20optional.)%20The%20company%20then%20uses%20that%20data%20%E2%80%94%20combined%20with%20demographic%20information%20participants%20provide%20%E2%80%94%20to%2C%20Zijderveld%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bstart%20segmenting%20how%20different%20populations%20are%20reacting%20to%20that%20content.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20like%20CBS%20and%20Disney%20can%20use%20this%20information%20to%20tailor%20their%20products%20based%20on%20how%20people%20are%20reacting%20to%20them.%20Maybe%20they%20recut%20a%20trailer%2C%20get%20rid%20of%20a%20joke%20that's%20not%20landing%2C%20or%20change%20an%20ad%20based%20on%20the%20demographics%20of%20the%20audience%20they're%20selling%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMonitoring%20employee%20emotions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20those%20applications%20may%20seem%20benign%20or%20even%20beneficial%2C%20the%20use%20of%20EAI%20in%20the%20workplace%20is%20much%20more%20fraught.%20Employees%20often%20don't%20realize%20it's%20being%20used%2C%20meaning%20they%20could%20be%20deemed%20unhappy%20at%20work%2C%20emotionally%20unstable%2C%20or%20too%20stressed%20to%20do%20their%20job%20without%20even%20knowing%20they%20were%20being%20surveilled%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhirevue-chief-growth-officer-shares-how-ai-supports-companies-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHireVue%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Utah%20recruitment%20platform%2C%20began%20using%20EAI%20facial%20analysis%20in%202014%20as%20part%20of%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhirevue-ai-powered-job-interview-platform-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecandidate%20interview%20process%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20idea%20behind%20the%20tech%20was%20noble%3A%20The%20EAI%20was%20supposed%20to%20mitigate%20bias%20and%20spot%20ideal%20candidates%20by%20identifying%20soft%20skills%2C%20cognitive%20ability%2C%20psychological%20traits%2C%20and%20emotional%20intelligence%20during%20video%20interviews.%20Hundreds%20of%20businesses%2C%20including%20Ikea%2C%20Dow%20Jones%2C%20and%20Oracle%2C%20used%20the%20software%20to%20assess%20more%20than%201%20million%20job%20seekers%2C%20The%20Washington%20Post%20reported.%20But%20in%202019%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fepic.org%2Fhirevue-facing-ftc-complaint-from-epic-halts-use-of-facial-recognition%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Electronic%20Privacy%20Information%20Center%20alleged%20%26quot%3Bunfair%20and%20deceptive%20practices%26quot%3B%20because%20HireVue's%20tech%20was%20not%20proven%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20what%20the%20company%20said%20it%20could.%20The%20complaint%20pointed%20to%20research%20that%20found%20facial%20analysis%20could%20be%20biased%20against%20women%2C%20people%20of%20color%2C%20and%20people%20with%20neurological%20differences%2C%20and%20argued%20that%20it%20shouldn't%20be%20used%20to%20make%20hiring%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20public%20outcry%2C%20the%20company%20said%20in%202021%20it%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fjob-screening-service-halts-facial-analysis-applicants%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estop%20the%20use%20of%20EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20facial%20analysis%20because%20it%20wasn't%20worth%20the%20concern%20but%20would%20continue%20analyzing%20speech%2C%20intonation%2C%20and%20behavior%20during%20interviews.%20According%20to%20the%20company%2C%20the%20verbal%20elements%20were%20enough%20to%20make%20conclusions%20about%20a%20candidate's%20emotional%20state.%20%26quot%3BAlgorithms%20do%20not%20see%20significant%20additional%20predictive%20power%20when%20nonverbal%20data%20is%20added%20to%20language%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fc0b03d1d-f72f-48a8-b342-b4a926109452%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20recruitment%20platforms%2C%20such%20as%20Retorio%2C%20a%20Munich%20%26quot%3Bbehavioral-intelligence%20platform%2C%26quot%3B%20use%20a%20combination%20of%20facial%20analysis%2C%20body-pose%20recognition%2C%20and%20voice%20analysis%20%26quot%3Bto%20create%20a%20personality%20trait%20and%20soft%20skill%20profile%20of%20candidates%2C%20allowing%20recruiters%20to%20make%20smarter%20sales%20recruitment%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company's%20website%20says.%20It%20also%20says%20that%20its%20tech%20removes%20bias%20and%20that%20the%20process%20is%20voluntary%20for%20candidates%2C%20who%20can%20opt%20out%20at%20any%20point%20before%20the%20video%20recording%20is%20sent%20to%20the%20hiring%20company%20and%20apply%20a%20different%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Myers%20West%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20the%20AI%20Now%20Institute%2C%20is%20skeptical%20of%20company%20claims%20that%20EAI%20is%20free%20of%20bias.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20scenario%20where%20you%20can%20go%20around%20making%20that%20kind%20of%20claim%20with%20any%20rigor%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20And%20while%20Retorio%20may%20emphasize%20the%20voluntary%20nature%20of%20its%20tech%2C%20the%20companies%20who%20license%20it%20could%20be%20discounting%20candidates%20who%20choose%20to%20not%20submit%20a%20video%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20hired%2C%20workers%20aren't%20free%20of%20emotion-recognition%20tech.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fthis-call-may-be-monitored-for-tone-and-emotion%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecall%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20EAI%20is%20already%20being%20used%20to%20pick%20up%20on%20the%20emotions%20of%20customer-service%20representatives%20and%20the%20customers%20on%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20line.%20It%20can%20give%20real-time%20feedback%20to%20workers%20on%20how%20they%20should%20adjust%20their%20tone%20to%20align%20with%20what%20the%20algorithms%20consider%20appropriate.%20This%20left%20some%20workers%20feeling%20confused%20by%20negative%20feedback%20and%20scared%20that%20the%20tech%20would%20get%20them%20in%20trouble%20if%20they%20didn't%20sound%20sufficiently%20positive%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdl.acm.org%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1145%2F3544548.3580950%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20found%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20other%20companies%20are%20racing%20to%20develop%20EAI-enabled%20gadgets%20to%20dig%20even%20deeper%20into%20employees'%20psyches.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frameryacoustics.com%2Fen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFramery%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20company%20that%20makes%20high-end%20office%20pods%20used%20by%20the%20likes%20of%20LinkedIn%20and%20Nvidia%2C%20has%20recently%20started%20testing%20an%20office%20chair%20embedded%20with%20biosensors.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20measure%20heart%20rate%2C%20heart-rate%20variability%2C%20breathing%20rate%2C%20and%20the%20nervousness%20of%20the%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Helsinki-based%20founder%20Samu%20H%C3%A4llfors%20said.%20Framery%20has%20also%20patented%20a%20tool%20to%20measure%20laughter%20based%20on%20just%20body%20movement.%20H%C3%A4llfors%20envisions%20that%20businesses%20will%20soon%20include%20employee%20well-being%20metrics%20in%20their%20corporate%20reporting.%20If%20that%20happens%2C%20Framery%20will%20be%20able%20to%20step%20in%20and%20anonymously%20compile%20data%20from%20its%20smart%20chairs%20to%20help%20companies%20determine%20the%20overall%20sentiment%20of%20their%20workplaces%20%E2%80%94%20and%20track%20when%20staffers%20are%20more%20stressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20West%20has%20questioned%20claims%20of%20keeping%20emotional%20data%20anonymous%3A%20%26quot%3BYou're%20dealing%20with%20identifiable%20data%20inherently%20if%20you're%20working%20with%20biometrics%20and%20emotion%20recognition.%26quot%3B%20She%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BThere's%20so%20many%20data%20streams%20that%20are%20being%20collected%20that%20the%20anonymization%20claim%20really%20breaks%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20founders%20of%20Looksery%2C%20a%20photo%20and%20software%20company%20owned%20by%20Snap%20Inc.%2C%20were%20granted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpatents.google.com%2Fpatent%2FUS9747573B2%2Fen%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epatent%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202017%20for%20videoconferencing%20technology%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3BEmotion%20Recognition%20For%20WorkForce.%26quot%3B%20While%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20it's%20being%20used%2C%20the%20patent%20covers%20emotion%20recognition%20for%20video%20calls%2C%20especially%20for%20call-center%20workers%2C%20and%20says%20unambiguously%20that%20%26quot%3Ban%20employer%20can%20use%20this%20information%20for%20workforce%20optimization%2C%20laying-off%20underperforming%20employees%2C%20promoting%20those%20employees%20that%20have%20positive%20attitudes%20towards%20customers%2C%20or%20making%20other%20administrative%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKat%20Roemmich%2C%20a%20Ph.D.%20student%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%20School%20of%20Information%20who%20has%20conducted%20research%20on%20EAI%2C%20has%20found%20that%20employees%20frequently%20remain%20unaware%20that%20their%20company%20is%20using%20the%20tech%20while%20they're%20on%20the%20job.%20In%20fact%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fainowinstitute.org%2Fpublication%2Fbiometric-surveillance-is-quietly-expanding%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethere's%20no%20requirement%20for%20employers%20to%20tell%20them%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Emotional%20information%20can%20be%20gathered%20by%20%26quot%3Banalyzing%20data%20that%20they%20already%20collect%20as%20part%20of%20existing%20monitoring%20and%20surveillance%20programs%2C%26quot%3B%20Roemmich%20said%2C%20meaning%20companies%20can%20just%20tack%20EAI%20onto%20existing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-companies-spy-on-employees-bossware-jpmorgan-amazon-monitor-rto-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurveillance%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20alerting%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rapid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmajority-remote-hybrid-work-companies-wfh-monitor-employees-rto-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpansion%20of%20surveillance%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20pandemic%20because%20of%20remote%20work%20has%20left%20more%20people%20exposed%20to%20the%20possibility%20of%20having%20their%20emotions%20tracked%20at%20work.%20Since%20EAI%20is%20not%20considered%20uniquely%20identifiable%20biometric%20data%20%E2%80%94%20the%20way%20a%20fingerprint%20or%20facial%20scan%20is%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20unregulated%20in%20the%20US.%20In%20Europe%2C%20the%20EU%20is%20working%20on%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20likely%20make%20it%20illegal%20in%20the%20workplace.%20But%20until%20there's%20regulation%2C%20companies%20are%20free%20to%20use%20it%20as%20they%20please.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPseudoscience%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20ethical%20problems%20of%20EAI%2C%20the%20tech%20faces%20another%20challenge%3A%20It%20may%20not%20even%20work.%20EAI%20that%20interprets%20facial%20expressions%20is%20often%20rooted%20in%20the%20American%20psychologist%20Paul%20Ekman's%20research%2C%20which%20proposed%20that%20core%20human%20emotions%20%E2%80%94%20fear%2C%20anger%2C%20joy%2C%20sadness%2C%20disgust%2C%20and%20surprise%20%E2%80%94%20were%20revealed%20through%20universal%20facial%20expressions%20transcending%20cultural%20differences.%20But%20Ekman's%20work%20has%20faced%20substantial%20pushback%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20consensus%20among%20scientists%20on%20the%20definition%20of%20specific%20human%20emotions%2C%20or%20how%20you%20could%20accurately%20read%20them%20on%20someone's%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202019%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F1529100619832930%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereview%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20available%20research%20on%20emotion%20recognition%20through%20facial%20analysis%20found%20that%20there%20was%20insufficient%20evidence%20for%20any%20link%20between%20facial%20expressions%20and%20emotions.%20The%20paper's%20authors%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BVery%20little%20is%20known%20about%20how%20and%20why%20certain%20facial%20movements%20express%20instances%20of%20emotion%2C%20particularly%20at%20a%20level%20of%20detail%20sufficient%20for%20such%20conclusions%20to%20be%20used%20in%20important%2C%20real-world%20applications.%26quot%3B%20They%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20different%20contexts%20and%20cultures%20could%20result%20in%20a%20huge%20variety%20of%20expressions%20for%20the%20same%20emotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEAI%20companies%20disagree.%20Zijderveld%20of%20Smart%20Eye%20said%20that%20the%20company's%20vast%20amounts%20of%20data%20from%20about%2090%20countries%20%26quot%3Ballows%20us%20to%20account%20for%20these%20cultural%20sensitivities.%26quot%3B%20She%20added%20that%20knowing%20context%20was%20clearly%20important%20to%20understanding%20the%20correlation%20between%20emotions%20and%20facial%20expressions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20industry's%20opaqueness%20makes%20it%20nearly%20impossible%20to%20obtain%20independent%20research-based%20proof%20of%20how%20the%20tech%20works.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20sticking%20point%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Roemmich%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can't%20get%20the%20framing%20of%20the%20debates%20right%20and%20the%20foundational%20issues%2C%20then%2C%20as%20we're%20already%20seeing%2C%20practitioners%20that%20use%20emotionality%20are%20going%20to%20disregard%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20tech%20can%20genuinely%20capture%20internal%20feelings%2C%20using%20it%20in%20work%20settings%20gives%20companies%20unprecedented%20access%20to%20the%20private%20emotions%20of%20their%20employees.%20And%20if%20it%20can't%2C%20then%20companies%20using%20EAI%20to%20make%20decisions%20about%20hiring%20or%20firing%20someone%20could%20be%20entirely%20misguided.%20Either%20way%2C%20it's%20a%20troubling%20indication%20of%20how%20companies%20are%20creeping%20into%20every%20part%20of%20our%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20even%20our%20innermost%20thoughts%20and%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fclem-de-pressigny%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EClem%20De%20Pressigny%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3Efreelance%20writer%20and%20editor%2C%20and%C2%A0previously%20the%20Editorial%20Director%20of%20i-D%20magazine.%20She%20covers%20the%20internet%20and%20technology%2C%20the%20climate%20crisis%20and%20culture.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-surveillance-detects-emotion-at-work-gets-you-fired-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700477161000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655657094ca513d8242ab520%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-surveillance-detects-emotion-at-work-gets-you-fired-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Companies%20are%20using%20emotion%20AI%20to%20surveil%20people%20at%20work.%20But%20some%20scien