0%E2%80%9Ckilling%20the%20constitution%20with%20a%20thousand%20cuts%E2%80%9D.%20In%20an%20interview%20published%20by%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E%20on%20November%2013%2C%20Khaitan%20describes%20the%20framework%20through%20which%20the%20state%20of%20democracy%20in%20a%20country%20can%20be%20assessed.%20His%20analysis%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20performance%20leads%20him%20to%20believe%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%20is%20in%20peril.%20Khaitan%20also%20discusses%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20first%20NDA%20regime%20and%20the%20second%20NDA%20regime%20are%20different.%20The%20first%2C%20he%20says%2C%20adopted%20a%20subtle%2C%20behind%20the%20scenes%20approach%20to%20go%20about%20its%20agenda.%20This%20allowed%20it%20to%20make%20changes%20quietly.%20But%20the%20second%20regime%20acquired%20a%20%E2%80%9Cswagger%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20has%20been%20more%20brazen%20in%20its%20agenda.%20This%20is%20also%20why%20several%20popular%20mobilisations%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%20protests%20against%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20and%20the%20farm%20laws%20%E2%80%93%20have%20cropped%20up%20during%20the%20second%20term%2C%20Khaitan%20says.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20is%20a%20full%20transcript%20of%20the%20interview%2C%20edited%20lightly%20for%20style%2C%20clarity%20and%20syntax.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHello%20and%20welcome%20to%20a%20special%20interview%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%20With%20elections%20due%20in%20six%20months%20in%20May%202024%20which%20will%20also%20mark%2010%20years%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%20as%20prime%20minister%20of%20India%2C%20we%20ask%20a%20question%20that%20many%20have%20been%20asking%20themselves.%20Has%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20imperilled%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%3F%20Joining%20me%20now%20from%20London%20is%20someone%20who%E2%80%99s%20thought%20carefully%20about%20this.%20He%E2%80%99s%20a%20professor%20of%20Public%20Law%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3ETarunabh%20Khaitan.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProfessor%20Khaitan%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20devised%20an%20analytical%20framework%20for%20studying%20when%20a%20democracy%20is%20in%20peril.%20That%20framework%20comprises%20three%20elements%20to%20do%20with%20how%20accountable%20is%20the%20executive.%20First%2C%20its%20accountability%20to%20the%20people.%20Second%2C%20its%20accountability%20to%20other%20state%20institutions%20like%20the%20opposition%20and%20the%20judiciary.%20Third%2C%20its%20accountability%20to%20the%20media%20academic%20criticism%20and%20civil%20society%20institutions.%20Can%20you%20start%20by%20explaining%20why%20this%20framework%20is%20the%20right%20way%20of%20judging%20whether%20democracy%20is%20in%20peril%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFirst%2C%20thank%20you%20Mr%20Thapar%20for%20having%20me%20here%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20pleasure%20to%20talk%20to%20you.%20So%2C%20the%20motivation%20behind%20this%20paper%20was%20to%20devise%20a%20framework%20that%E2%80%99s%20fair%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20the%20government%20in%20power.%20What%20we%20would%20not%20do%20for%20this%20purpose%20is%20a%20framework%20that%20criticises%20the%20policies%20of%20the%20government%20simply%20because%20I%20may%20not%20like%20them.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20elected%20legitimate%20government%20with%20a%20mandate%20to%20implement%20its%20policies%2C%20whatever%20ideological%20spectrum%20they%20come%20from.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20the%20task%20was%20to%20devise%20a%20framework%20that%20distinguishes%20policy%20differences%20from%20a%20constitutional%20and%20democratic%20foundational%20undermining.%20And%20that%20is%20what%20this%20framework%20tries%20to%20do%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%2C%20it%20does%20not%20go%20after%20what%20is%20the%20ideological%20makeup%20of%20this%20government%2C%20what%20policies%20it%20wants%20to%20implement%2C%20but%20the%20question%20is%20this%3A%20Does%20this%20government%20seek%20to%20fuse%20the%20ruling%20party%20with%20the%20state%3F%20Because%20as%20we%20know%20a%20famous%20political%20scientist%20once%20defined%20democracy%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20system%20in%20which%20parties%20lose%20elections%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20if%20the%20government%20is%20doing%20things%20which%20make%20it%20harder%20for%20the%20ruling%20party%20to%20lose%20elections%20by%20entrenching%20it%20within%20the%20framework%20of%20the%20state%2C%20that%20was%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eproblem.%20And%20if%20the%20executive%20which%20in%20my%20discipline%20in%20constitutional%20theory%2C%20we%20call%20it%20the%20most%20dangerous%20branch%20because%20it%20is%20the%20branch%20of%20the%20state%20that%20holds%20military%20power%2C%20that%20holds%20police%20power%2C%20right%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20got%20the%20power%20of%20the%20sword.%20So%20the%20executive%20being%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20dangerous%20branch%E2%80%9D%20is%20subject%20to%20a%20series%20of%20checks%20in%20a%20democracy%2C%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20it%20does%20not%20do%20the%20things%20that%20it%20can%20do%20and%20undermine%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20that%20was%20the%20framework%20I%20sought%20to%20design%20and%20hence%20the%20three%20typical%20accountability%20mechanisms%20that%20all%20democracies%20%E2%80%93%20all%20real%20democracies%20around%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20subject%20the%20executive%20to.%20Accountability%20to%20the%20people%20here%20and%20now.%20Accountability%20to%20state%20institutions%20which%20do%20two%20things%20%E2%80%93%20ensure%20that%20the%20government%20is%20accountable%20not%20only%20to%20the%20people%20today%2C%20but%20to%20future%20people.%20Even%20if%20all%20the%20people%20of%20India%20today%20unanimously%20decide%20that%20we%20should%20become%20an%20authoritarian%20regime%2C%20even%20then%20that%20would%20reduce%20or%20take%20away%20the%20democratic%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erights%20of%20future%20Indians%20and%20therefore%20impermissible%2C%20even%20to%20the%20people.%20And%20institutions%20ensure%20that%20%E2%80%93%20institutions%20like%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20institutions%20like%20the%20Election%20Commission%20%E2%80%93%20ensure%20that%20the%20rights%2C%20democratic%20rights%20of%20future%20people%20are%20ensured.%20And%20because%20we%20never%20have%20unanimity%20in%20a%20democracy%2C%20other%20institutions%20as%20well%20as%20the%20media%2C%20the%20universities%20ensure%20that%20there%20is%20continuing%20democracy%20in%20between%20elections.%20Because%20democracy%20is%20not%20just%20elections%20every%20five%20years%2C%20right%3F%20So%2C%20how%20do%20you%20keep%20the%20government%20continuously%20accountable%3F%20By%20asking%20tough%20questions.%20So%20that%20is%20a%20framework%20of%20democracy%20and%20that%20was%20the%20metric%2C%20the%20measure%2C%20by%20which%20I%20sought%20to%20judge%20this%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FsLRO4qs6Q-Q%3Fsi%3D2xigJHEpxNUvGcc_%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20Professor%20Khaitan%20you%20applied%20your%20framework%20to%20the%20first%20Modi%20government%20which%20served%20from%202014%20to%202019.%20I%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20the%20second%20Modi%20government%20afterwards.%20But%20with%20specific%20reference%20to%20the%20first%20government%2C%20you%20write%20it%20did%20indeed%20seek%20to%20undermine%20each%20of%20these%20three%20strands%20of%20executive%20accountability.%20You%20say%20its%20mode%20of%20operation%20was%20subtle%2C%20indirect%20and%20incremental%20but%20also%20systemic.%20And%20you%20say%20this%20amounts%20to%20%E2%80%9Ckilling%20a%20constitution%20by%20a%20thousand%20cuts%E2%80%9D.%20Before%20we%20come%20to%20details%2C%20can%20you%20explain%20this%20further%2C%20this%20conclusion%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EO%3Cspan%3Ef%20course.%20So%2C%20there%20are%20no%20tanks%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20Delhi.%20The%20media%20is%20supposedly%20still%20free%2C%20the%20broadcasting%20tower%20has%20not%20been%20taken%20over%20by%20the%20government.%20There%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20state%20of%20emergency%2C%20the%20military%20is%20not%20on%20the%20streets.%20So%2C%20it%20does%20not%20feel%20like%20a%2020th-century%20emergency.%20Now%2C%20before%20I%20directly%20respond%20to%20the%20question%20in%20the%20Indian%20context%2C%20I%20should%20locate%20it%20in%20a%20global%20context.%20Autocratic%20leaders%20of%20the%2020th%20century%20have%20become%20smarter.%20They%20have%20learned%20from%20the%20failures%20of%20what%20we%20used%20to%20call%20%E2%80%9Cdictators%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%2020th%20century.%20Twentieth-century%20dictators%20were%20in%20your%20face%2C%20direct%20and%20they%20launched%20typically%20a%20full%20frontal%20assault%20on%20democracy.%20And%20the%20signs%20would%20be%20obvious%2C%20they%20would%20be%20visible.%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20emergency%20is%20a%20clear%20example%20of%20that%20kind%20of%20in-your-face%2C%20visible%2C%20full-frontal%20assault%20on%20democracy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20at%20least%20since%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century%20but%20actually%20typically%2C%20this%20happened%20after%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Berlin%20Wall%2C%20democracy%20has%20become%20the%20key%20metric%20for%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20a%20government.%20It%E2%80%99s%20become%20much%20harder%20for%20a%20state%20to%20justify%20itself%2C%20to%20legitimise%20itself%20internationally%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20seen%20to%20be%20democratic.%20So%20latterday%20autocrats%20have%20learned%20that%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20do%20all%20of%20those%20direct%2C%20full-frontal%20things.%20In%20fact%2C%20most%20of%20their%20agenda%20can%20still%20be%20realised%20while%20retaining%20the%20paraphernalia%20of%20democracy%2C%20by%20going%20through%20the%20motions%20of%20democracy%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20this%20is%20not%20just%20an%20Indian%20phenomenon.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAcross%20the%20world%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20in%20countries%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Elike%20Poland%2C%20Hungary%2C%20Brazil%20under%20%5BJair%5D%20Bolsonaro%2C%20South%20Africa%20under%20%5BJacob%5D%20Zuma%2C%20the%20US%20under%20Donald%20Trump.%20In%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20these%20countries%2C%20we%20have%20seen%20a%20similar%20incremental%2C%20subtle%20but%20systemic%20style%20of%20autocratisation%20where%20you%20chip%20away%20at%20the%20foundations%20of%20democracy%20instead%20of%20launching%20a%20full-scale%2C%20full-frontal%20assault.%20That%20is%20the%20idea%20behind%20the%20thousand%20cuts.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20one%20single%20big%20assault%20like%20the%2042nd%20Amendment%20was%20and%20the%20Declaration%20of%20Emergency%20was%20under%20Indira%20Gandhi.%20We%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20micro-assaults%20which%20make%20it%20harder%20to%20see%20and%20harder%20to%20mobilise%20against.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20to%20put%20it%20metaphorically%20and%20colloquially%2C%20this%20is%20not%20%3Cem%3Ehalal%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3Ejhatka%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20as%20you%20call%20it%20%E2%80%98death%20by%20a%20thousand%20cuts%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20each%20little%20cut%20incrementally%20adds%20up%20to%20a%20further%20imperilling%20of%20democracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndeed%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20good%20metaphor.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlright%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20then%20come%20to%20the%20details.%20Between%202014%20and%202019%2C%20India%20has%20held%20regular%20elections%20both%20at%20the%20state%20and%20at%20the%20national%20level.%20The%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20party%20has%20won%20some%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20lost%20some%20and%20this%20has%20happened%20multiple%20times.%20So%2C%20on%20what%20grounds%20do%20you%20say%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20been%20accountable%20to%20the%20people%3F%20Many%20would%20say%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20holds%20elections%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20accepts%20its%20defeat%2C%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20accountability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndeed.%20So%2C%20we%20must%20first%20understand%20that%20accountability%20is%20not%20a%20binary%20%E2%80%9Ceither%2C%20or%E2%80%9D%20phenomenon.%20Accountability%20is%20a%20scalar%20concept.%20You%20can%20have%20more%20or%20less%20of%20it%20and%20what%20we%20have%20seen%20is%20a%20gradual%20reduction%20in%20accountability%20on%20all%20three%20fronts%20and%20your%20question%20concerns%20the%20first%20front%2C%20which%20is%20electoral%20accountability%2C%20directly%20to%20the%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20what%20are%20the%20things%20that%20the%20first%20Modi%20regime%20did%20or%20tried%20to%20do%20to%20undermine%20that%20accountability%20to%20the%20people%3F%20I%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20the%20paper%20later%20that%20discusses%20the%20things%20that%20have%20happened%20with%20the%20Election%20Commission%20and%20some%20credible%20grounds%20to%20worry%20about%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eeven-handedness%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20in%20scheduling%20elections%20in%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20it%20held%20elections.%20But%20I%20put%20that%20to%20one%20side%20for%20now.%20There%20are%20three%20key%20things%20which%20the%20first%20regime%20did%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20two%20quite%20successfully%2C%20and%20the%20third%20was%20a%20thought%20balloon%20which%20might%20actually%20fructuate%20before%20the%20end%20of%20this%20parliament.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20important%20thing%20was%20a%20concerted%20effort%20to%20delegitimise%20and%20disenfranchise%20the%20Muslim%20minority%20population%20of%20India.%20Now%2C%20as%20we%20know%20not%20all%20Hindus%20vote%20for%20the%20BJP%20but%20very%20few%20Muslims%20do%20because%20of%20its%20anti-Muslim%20political%20stance.%20We%20saw%20a%20whole%20range%20of%20efforts%20%E2%80%93%20the%20most%20important%20and%20the%20biggest%20amongst%20them%20was%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizenship%20exercise%20in%20Assam%2C%20which%20although%20on%20its%20face%20was%20neutral%20in%20terms%20of%20religion%20and%20indeed%20ordered%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20by%20the%20judiciary.%20But%20this%20is%20an%20opportunist%20government%20which%20you%20know%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EBehti%20Ganga%20mein%20haath%20dhona.%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20It%20saw%20an%20opportunity%20and%20ran%20with%20it.%20It%E2%80%99s%20the%20rhetoric%20around%20the%20NRC%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhich%20was%20communalised%20in%20an%20astonishing%20way%2C%20especially%20by%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Assam%2C%20who%20talked%20about%20this%20as%20ensuring%20that%20the%20indigenous%20people%20of%20Assam%20%5Bprevail%5D.%20The%20dog%20whistle%20politics%20around%20it%20was%20clearly%20anti-Muslim%20and%20polarising.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20that%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20the%20only%20anti-Muslim%20phenomenon.%20As%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20whole%20host%20of%20laws%20that%20were%20passed%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20in%20BJP-ruled%20states%20%E2%80%93%20which%20ensured%20or%20sought%20to%20ensure%20a%20second-class%20citizenship%20status%20for%20Muslims%2C%20including%20myriad%20anti-conversion%20laws%2C%20myriad%20laws%20to%20stop%20%E2%80%9Clove%20jihad%E2%80%9D%2C%20myriad%20laws%20about%20cow%20slaughter.%20So%20an%20entire%20generation%20of%2C%20especially%20young%2C%20Muslim%20men%20being%20targeted%20and%20criminalised%20in%20ways%20that%20we%20have%20not%20seen%20in%20India%20before%20and%20perhaps%20more%20akin%20to%20the%20criminalisation%20of%20young%20black%20men%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20that%20was%20the%20first%20dimension%20of%20electoral%20accountability.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%20was%20talked%20about%2C%20discussed%20and%20proposed%20in%20the%20first%20regime%20but%20it%20actually%20was%20not%20enacted%20until%20the%20second%20regime.%20But%20it%20did%20help%20with%20polarisation%20of%20the%20electorate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20question%20and%20much%20more%20meaningful%20in%20its%20impact%20on%20Indian%20politics%20was%20the%202017%20finance%20Bill%20which%20through%20a%20surreptitious%20money%20Bill%20route%20to%20override%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20veto%20not%20only%20retrospectively%20overturned%20judicial%20decisions%20that%20had%20found%20both%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress%20to%20have%20violated%20campaign%20finance%20laws%20but%20also%20granted%20full%20anonymity%20to%20parties%20in%20securing%20electoral%20bonds.%20And%20this%20was%20dual%20anonymity%20because%20you%20would%20not%20know%20who%20the%20donors%20are%2C%20you%20do%20not%20know%20who%20the%20parties%20are.%20Now%2C%20of%20course%2C%20we%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eknow%20through%20the%20proceedings%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20only%20partial%20anonymity.%20Why%3F%20Because%20the%20ruling%20party%20knows%20who%20is%20donating%20money%20to%20which%20party.%20But%20the%20opposition%20does%20not%20know%20who%20is%20donating%20money%20to%20which%20party.%20Now%20in%20a%20context%20in%20which%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esupporting%20the%20opposition%20is%20risky%20business%2C%20this%20has%20completely%20changed%20the%20scenario%20in%20which%20party%20funding%20works%20in%20India.%20There%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20evidence%20%E2%80%93%20from%20self-declaration%20by%20parties%2C%20from%20reports%20by%20the%20RBI%20and%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20which%20issues%20these%20bonds%20and%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%E2%80%99%20own%20research%20%E2%80%93%20that%20most%20of%20the%20funding%20is%20coming%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecorporates.%20We%20know%20that%20because%20of%20the%20size%20of%20the%20bonds%20being%20bought%20which%20are%20in%20the%20crores%2C%20not%20the%20lakhs.%20Just%20to%20give%20you%20one%20statistic%20in%20the%20financial%20year%20of%202017-%2018%2C%20over%2095%25%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20purchased%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20it%20formed%20a%20huge%20proportion%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20overall%20funding.%20So%2C%20this%20kind%20of%E2%80%A6%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20even%20tilting%20the%20field.%20It%E2%80%99s%20almost%20squeezing%20out%20the%20opposition%20from%20any%20financial%20breathing%20space%20within%20the%20electoral%20field.%20And%20as%20we%20know%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20taken%20its%20time%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20third%20element%3F%20Because%20you%20said%20three%20elements%20account%20for%20accountability.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20third%20was%20the%20thought%20balloon%20about%20simultaneous%20polls%20which%20we%20now%20know%20has%20been%20put%20into%20full%20gear.%20And%20that%20has%20two%20bad%20effects%20on%20electoral%20accountability.%20The%20first%20is%2C%20that%20it%20moves%20the%20system%20closer%20to%20a%20presidential%20model.%20We%20know%20that%20the%E2%80%A6.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20happened%20as%20yet.%20It%E2%80%99s%20only%20been%20talked%20about.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%2C%20it%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20happened%20yet.%20I%20think%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20let%E2%80%99s%20then%20leave%20this%20discussion%20for%20Modi%202%2C%20because%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20more%20germane%20to%20Modi%202.%20But%20I%E2%80%99ll%20recap%20for%20the%20audience%20the%20two%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20made%20itself%20less%20accountable%20to%20the%20people.%20One%20is%20through%20the%20whole%20set%20of%20discriminatory%20laws%20that%20target%20the%20Muslim%20community%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20virtually%2015%25%20of%20our%20population%20pretty%20close%20to%20200%20million.%20And%20the%20second%20is%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20which%20confer%20the%20shroud%20of%20anonymity%20both%20on%20donors%20and%20on%20recipients%20and%20the%20major%20recipient%2C%20as%20you%20said%20in%202017%2C%2094%25%20was%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20then%20come%20to%20the%20second%20point%20the%20second%20point.%20The%20second%20point%20is%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20accountability%20to%20state%20institutions%20like%20the%20opposition%20and%20the%20judiciary.%20Most%20people%20would%20certainly%20readily%20accept%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20is%20hardly%20accountable%20to%20the%20opposition.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20accountable%20to%20the%20opposition%20at%20all.%20But%20what%20about%20accountability%20to%20the%20judiciary%3F%20Where%20has%20the%20Modi%20government%20failed%20on%20that%20count%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20so%20one%20of%20the%20first%20acts%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%20%E2%80%93%20and%20this%20was%20by%20the%20way%20with%20the%20support%20of%20perhaps%20a%20naive%20opposition%20because%20these%20were%20still%20early%20days%20and%20they%20thought%20this%20was%20going%20to%20be%20government%20as%20usual%20%E2%80%93%20was%20the%20constitutional%20amendment%20to%20change%20the%20judicial%20appointment%20system%20and%20one%20of%20the%20features%20of%20the%20new%20appointment%20committee%20was%20a%20much%20more%20stronger%20role%20to%20the%20executive%20government%20in%20appointing%20judges.%20Now%2C%20as%20we%20know%20that%20was%20struck%20down%20by%20the%20courts%20and%20the%20%5BSupreme%5D%20Court%20said%20it%20is%20going%20to%20retain%20the%20system%20of%20self-appointment%20of%20the%20judiciary%20through%20the%20collegium%20system.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhat%20has%20happened%20since%20is%20astonishing%E2%80%A6%20and%20since%20Indira%20Gandhi%20an%20unprecedented%20way%20in%20which%20the%20government%20has%20rejected%2C%20resisted%2C%20sat%20on%2C%20exercised%20pocket%20veto%2C%20of%20judicial%20nominees%20across%20the%20board%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%20high%20court%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20It%20seems%20as%20if%20every%20single%20judicial%20appointment%20matters%20to%20this%20government%20in%20a%20huge%20way.%20And%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20kinds%20of%20judges%20that%20are%20being%20rejected%2C%20whose%20appointment%20is%20being%20stopped%20by%20the%20government%2C%20they%20are%20judges%20who%20have%20a%20reputation%20for%20being%20independent%20or%20have%20found%20in%20cases%20decisions%20or%20given%20judgments%20that%20have%20gone%20against%20the%20ruling%20party.%20So%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20I%20think%20remarkably%20unprecedented%20since%20at%20least%20the%20late%2080s%20in%20India.%20The%20second%20effort%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecompromise%20the%20judiciary%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20I%20just%20interrupt%3F%20There%E2%80%99s%20no%20doubt%20that%20the%20point%20you%E2%80%99re%20making%20is%20absolutely%20correct.%20The%20government%20has%20stalled%E2%80%A6%20sometimes%2C%20they%20simply%20refused%20to%20respond%20to%20nominations%20given%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20it%20sat%20on%20them%20for%20not%20just%20months%20but%20even%20years%20at%20a%20time.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20remedy%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20not%20exercised%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20the%20power%20of%20contempt.%20It%20could%20have%20acted%20against%20the%20law%20minister%20or%20the%20law%20secretary.%20It%E2%80%99s%20threatened%20on%20occasion%20by%20suggestion%20that%20it%20might.%20But%20it%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20done%20it.%20So%2C%20although%20the%20government%20has%20impinged%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20isn%E2%80%99t%20it%20equally%20true%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20the%20power%20to%20fight%20back%20and%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20exercised%20it%3F%20And%20that%20suggests%20that%20when%20it%E2%80%99s%20pushing%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20happy%20to%20be%20pushed%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20absolutely%20true.%20It%20is%20actually%20quite%20an%20indictment%20of%20our%20court.%20Now%20we%20should%20not%20expect%20a%20lot%20of%20courts%20in%20a%20democracy%2C%20the%20court%E2%80%A6%20or%20in%20any%20system%20actually%2C%20the%20court%20is%20the%20least%20dangerous%20branch.%20The%20only%20power%20it%20has%20is%20the%20power%20of%20the%20pen%20and%20ultimately%20enforcement%20of%20judicial%20orders%20remains%20with%20the%20executive.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20point%20I%20was%20about%20to%20mention%20about%20courts%20is%20the%20executive%20has%20simply%20ignored%20judicial%20orders%2C%20like%20in%20the%20Aadhaar%20case%20about%20not%20making%20it%20mandatory.%20So%20if%20the%20judiciary%20sees%20its%20orders%20that%20go%20against%20the%20government%20being%20ignored%2C%20there%20comes%20another%20big%20question%20before%20the%20courts.%20How%20far%20can%20they%20push%20and%20completely%20make%20the%20institution%20a%20laughing%20stock%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20third%20thing%20they%E2%80%99ve%20done%20is%20politically%20reward%20judges%20after%20retirement%20by%20giving%20them%20governorships%2C%20by%20making%20them%20MPs%20in%20parliament.%20We%20know%20about%20the%20infamous%20press%20conference%20in%202018%2C%20%5Bthe%20investigation%20into%20judge%20Loya%E2%80%99s%20death%5D%20that%20led%20to%20the%20press%20conference%2C%20where%20very%20senior%20judges%20were%20talking%20about%20how%20there%20was%20something%20rotten%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Denmark.%20The%20open%20call%20in%202018%20to%20defy%20the%20Sabarimala%20judgment%20in%20Kerala.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20of%20this%20creates%20an%20atmosphere%2C%20a%20signal%20to%20the%20judges%20that%20this%20government%20is%20going%20to%20fight%20back.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20going%20to%20abide%20by%20the%20usual.%20So%2C%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20courts%20rely%20on%20a%20sense%20of%20constitutional%20civility%20or%20we%20can%20call%20it%20constitutional%20shame.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20way%20of%20doing%20things.%20You%20do%20certain%20things%20not%20because%20any%20other%20consequence%20will%20follow%20but%20because%20you%20live%20in%20a%20civil%20society%20where%20when%20your%20neighbour%20needs%20help%2C%20you%20offer%20that%20help%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20civil%20to%20do%20that.%20Governments%20that%20don%E2%80%99t%20care%20about%20it%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20courts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%E2%80%99re%20saying%20that%20in%20its%20defiance%20of%20the%20court%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20rhetorical%20or%20in%20terms%20of%20action%20%E2%80%93%20this%20government%20has%20been%20so%20lacking%20in%20civility%20to%20be%20almost%20%E2%80%93%20forgive%20my%20using%20that%20word%20%E2%80%93%20shameless%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOh%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20it%E2%80%99s%20been%20totally%20constitutionally%20shameless.%20And%20even%20a%20brave%20court%20has%20to%20be%20a%20pragmatic%20court.%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20defending%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20things%20could%20have%20been%20nipped%20in%20the%20bud%20if%20the%20court%20drew%20a%20hard%20line%20right%20from%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebeginning.%20Because%20the%20government%20also%20becomes%20more%20brazen%20once%20it%20knows%20that%20it%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20get%20away%20with%20things.%20So%20the%20more%20the%20court%20steps%20back%2C%20the%20more%20it%E2%80%99s%20an%20institutional%20fight.%20But%20you%20know%2C%20as%20the%20court%20itself%20is%20changing%20character%20with%20more%20pro-government%20appointees%2C%20this%20will%20change%20too.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20the%20third%20level%20of%20accountability%20is%20to%20the%20media%2C%20to%20academic%20critics%2C%20to%20the%20universities%20and%20to%20civil%20society%20organisations.%20Again%2C%20many%20people%20would%20agree%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20failed%20to%20be%20accountable%20at%20this%20level%20to%20all%20three%20of%20the%20institutions%20I%E2%80%99ve%20mentioned.%20Would%20you%20accept%20that%20this%20is%20where%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20deliberate%20lack%20of%20accountability%20becomes%20most%20glaring%20of%20all%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20would%20agree%20with%20that.%20I%20should%20qualify%20my%20response%20by%20saying%20that%20the%20legal%20and%20judicial%20record%20of%20protection%20of%20civil%20liberties%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20press%20freedom%2C%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20free%20speech%2C%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20freedom%20of%20association%2C%20freedom%20of%20movement%2C%20things%20that%20Civil%20Society%20needs%20to%20flourish%20%E2%80%93%20has%20never%20been%20particularly%20strong.%20We%20have%20always%20had%20a%20lackadaisical%20judicial%20approach%20to%20civil%20liberties.%20The%20reason%20why%20these%20things%20nonetheless%20flourished%20was%20because%20the%20governments%20in%20the%20past%20have%20again%20been%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erelatively%20benign%20and%20relatively%20civil%20in%20their%20engagement%20with%20civil%20societies.%20They%20%3Cem%3Ewould%3C%2Fem%3E%20go%20after%20certain%20types%20of%20activities%20but%20the%20bar%20for%20that%20kind%20of%20%E2%80%98lawfare%E2%80%99%20or%20even%20illegal%20violence%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eagainst%20civil%20society%20actors%20was%20quite%20high%20with%20previous%20governments.%20This%20government%20has%20lowered%20the%20bar%20enormously.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20anti-state%20activities%20or%20separatist%20activities%20%E2%80%93%20which%20would%20trigger%20violence%20from%20previous%20governments.%20Anti-party%20activities%2C%20anti-party%20statements%2C%20anti-government%2C%20anti-prime%20minister%20statements%20are%20enough%20to%20trigger%20not%20only%20the%20legal%20machinery%20but%20also%20the%20violence.%20It%E2%80%99s%20the%20violence%2C%20the%20naked%20criminality%20of%20going%20after%20journalists%2C%20after%20students%2C%20after%20activists%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20Gauri%20Lankesh%20murder%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eor%20the%20violence%20against%20JNU%20students%20or%20how%20the%20CAA%20protests%20were%20handled.%20That%20also%20sets%20India%20apart%20in%20the%20global%20scene%2C%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20naked%20use%20of%20violence%20that%20is%20distinctive%20against%20civil%20society%20in%20the%20Indian%20case%20and%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20really%20quite%20appalling.%20Even%2010%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20any%20of%20us%20you%20or%20I%20would%20have%20imagined%20India%20would%20be%20where%20it%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etoday%20%E2%80%93%20where%20any%20of%20us%20saying%20anything%20in%20public%20have%20to%20think%20twice%20about%20whether%20we%E2%80%99ll%20get%20away%20with%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F10130903%2F640px-thumbnail.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F10130903%2F640px-thumbnail.jpg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F10130903%2F640px-thumbnail-300x183.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-662448%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22391%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20with%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah.%20Photo%3A%20PMO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWould%20you%20say%20that%20the%20treatment%20of%20journalists%2C%20just%20to%20pick%20on%20that%20in%20particular%2C%20under%20Modi%20is%20worse%20than%20the%20treatment%20of%20journalists%20under%20the%20Emergency%3F%20Because%20this%20is%20insidious%20and%20creeping%20and%20it%20imposes%20people%20to%20want%20to%20censor%20themselves%20for%20fear%20of%20what%20will%20be%20the%20consequences.%20Its%20worse%20than%20the%20outright%20in-your-face%20censorship%20of%2075.%20Would%20you%20agree%20with%20that%20or%20would%20you%20disagree%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20would%20give%20a%20complicated%20answer%20to%20that.%20In%20one%20sense%2C%20the%20emergency%20was%20much%20worse%20because%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20in%20prison%2C%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20anything%20at%20all.%20If%20there%20is%20clear%20censorship%2C%20then%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20write%20anything.%20But%20what%20is%20different%20with%20the%20Modi%20regime%20across%20the%20board%20is%20this%20very%20insidiousness.%20One%2C%20it%20creates%20a%20climate%20of%20fear%20where%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20where%20the%20line%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eis.%20Even%20in%20the%20Emergency%2C%20the%20line%20was%20relatively%20clear.%20You%20knew%20what%20not%20to%20cross.%20Here%2C%20the%20self-censorship%20becomes%20particularly%20important.%20And%20second%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20hard%20to%20mobilise%20and%20find%20allies%20against%20what%E2%80%99s%20going%20on%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20see%20what%E2%80%99s%20going%20on.%20You%20know%20it%E2%80%99s%20again%20the%20chipping%20away%2C%20the%20minor%20cut.%20So%2C%20in%20that%20sense%2C%20it%20is%20worse%20than%20the%20emergency%20because%20the%20people%20of%20India%20had%20no%20doubt%20about%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20Emergency%20and%20they%20threw%20Indra%20Gandhi%20out%20of%20power%20in%20the%20election%20that%20followed.%20That%20narrative%20is%20much%20harder%20to%20build%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuite%20right%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20happening%20behind%20closed%20doors%20in%20journalist%20offices%20or%20sometimes%20even%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20journalists.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20happening%20in%20a%20way%20in%20which%20the%20public%20readily%20recognises.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECan%20I%20just%20mention%20one%20more%20point%20here%20Karan%2C%20which%20is%20the%20use%20of%20corporate%20power%20to%20silence%20media%20as%20well.%20The%20government%20through%20its%20crony%20capitalist%2C%20through%20its%20capitalist%20friends%2C%20has%20also%20been%20buying%20up%20dissenting%20media%20houses%20which%20is%20a%20global%20phenomenon.%20It%E2%80%99s%20been%20used%20very%20effectively%20in%20India%20as%20well.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20also%20I%20might%20add%20the%20government%20uses%20corporate%20plans%20another%20way%20it%20sends%20signals%20to%20advertisers%20that%20a%20particular%20programme%20or%20a%20particular%20channel%20is%20not%20considered%20friendly%2C%20thus%20indicating%20we%20would%20prefer%20you%20not%20to%20support%20or%20advertise%20on%20this.%20And%20most%20corporates%20fall%20in%20line%20with%20the%20government%20because%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20endanger%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20relationship%20with%20the%20government.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20then%20take%20an%20overview%20of%20this%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Epoint%20of%20the%20Modi%20first%20government%20from%202014%20to%202019.%20You%20write%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%2C%20%E2%80%9CInstitutional%20mechanisms%20are%20undermined%20when%20their%20power%20relative%20to%20the%20political%20executive%20is%20diminished.%20They%20are%20captured%20when%20party%20loyalists%20take%20over%20the%20functioning%20of%20these%20institutions%20and%20make%20them%20pliant%20to%20the%20executive.%E2%80%9D%20Which%20of%20the%20two%20applies%20to%20the%20first%20Modi%20government%3F%20Have%20they%20undermined%20institutions%20or%20captured%20them%3F%20Or%20possibly%20done%20both%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20depends%20on%20the%20institution.%20So%20the%20institutions%20that%20were%20relatively%20easier%20to%20capture%20were%20those%20that%20were%20directly%20within%20the%20gift%20of%20the%20executive.%20So%20things%20like%20governor%E2%80%99s%20offices%2C%20the%20CBI%2C%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20which%20have%20been%20misused%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eprevious%20governments%2C%20but%20not%20to%20the%20same%20extent%20and%20not%20for%20such%20a%20low%20threshold%20trigger%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20been%20doing.%20The%20naked%20blatant%20partisanship%20that%20we%20are%20seeing%20is%20quite%20different.%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20quite%20appropriate%20to%20say%20that%20these%20institutions%20have%20been%20captured%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20even%20when%20compared%20to%20previous%20governments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20whole%20host%20of%20other%20accountability-seeking%20mechanisms%20I%20think%20have%20been%20undermined%20in%20the%20first%20regime.%20We%20talked%20about%20the%20courts%E2%80%A6%20but%20also%20the%20whole%20host%20of%20what%20are%20called%20fourth%20branch%20or%20guarantor%20institutions%20like%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20the%20RBI%20and%20various%20accountability-seeking%20bodies.%20Capturing%20is%20the%20endpoint%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20goal.%20You%20undermine%20and%20you%20chip%20away%20and%20eventually%2C%20you%20come%20to%20control%20the%20institution%20either%20financially%20or%20through%20the%20personnel.%20So%2C%20they%20lie%20on%20a%20spectrum.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20I%20imagine%20the%20treatment%20of%20parliament%20and%20in%20fact%20of%20parliamentary%20select%20committees%20is%20a%20particularly%20worrying%20example%20of%20how%20a%20major%20institution%20is%20undermined.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbsolutely%2C%20absolutely.%20And%20we%E2%80%99ve%20only%20recently%20last%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eweek%20seen%20the%20appalling%20unconstitutional%20conduct%20of%20the%20ethics%20committee%20in%20the%20Mahua%20Moitra%20case.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%2C%20you%20say%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20sought%20to%20legitimise%20its%20undermining%20and%20capturing%20of%20institutions%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20that%20I%20want%20to%20turn%20to%20at%20this%20moment.%20You%20say%20this%20legitimization%20has%20happened%20(a)%20through%20its%20discourse%20of%20hyper-nationalism%3B%20secondly%2C%20through%20its%20promised%20property%20decisiveness%20and%20efficiency%20and%20thirdly%2C%20through%20what%20you%20call%20%E2%80%9Cits%20welfarist%20developmental%20populist%20discourse%E2%80%9D.%20Are%20you%20saying%20that%20nationalism%2C%20Hindutva%20and%20populist%20welfare%20policies%20are%20the%20facade%20or%20disguise%20behind%20which%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20deliberately%20eroded%20and%20imperilled%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%3F%20This%20has%20provided%20the%20screen%20behind%20which%20they%E2%80%99ve%20gone%20on%20to%20do%20whatever%20they%20wanted%20to%20do.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20I%20would%20say%20that.%20I%20think%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20key%20difference%20between%20M%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eodi%E2%80%99s%20style%20of%20authoritarianism%20and%20say%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20authoritarianism%20in%20the%20US.%20For%20the%20Trump%20regime%2C%20power%20was%20its%20own%20reward.%20Trump%20would%20say%20and%20do%20whatever%20would%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ekeep%20him%20in%20power.%20The%20Modi%20government%2C%20the%20BJP%20in%20power%2C%20is%20a%20committed%20ideological%20party%20and%20its%20agenda%20of%20Hindutva%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20to%20translate%20India%20into%20Hindu%20rashtra%20%E2%80%93%20is%20central.%20It%E2%80%99s%20genuinely%20committed%20to%20that%20agenda.%20Now%20the%20Hindu%20rashtra%20is%20democratic%20in%20a%20limited%20sense.%20So%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20part%20of%20the%20agenda%20of%20making%20India%20into%20a%20Hindu%20Rashtra%20is%20that%20democracy%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebecomes%20what%20Southeast%20Asian%20Nations%20have%20called%20a%20guided%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20opposition%20works%20in%20a%20very%20constrained%2C%20limited%20space%3B%20there%20is%20a%20hegemonic%20ruling%20party.%20So%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20brag%20about%2050%20years%20of%20BJP%20rule%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20political%20bragging.%20I%20think%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethere%20is%20a%20concerted%2C%20systemic%2C%20strategic%20effort%20to%20bring%20that%20about.%20I%20think%20undermining%20democracy%20and%20Hindutva%20are%20part%20of%20the%20same%20coin%2C%20hand%20in%20hand.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EForgive%20my%20interrupting.%20So%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%20is%20Hindutva%20is%20not%20a%20facade%20or%20a%20disguise%2C%20it%20is%20the%20actual%20intent%20of%20the%20government.%20And%20a%20corollary%20of%20that%20intent%20is%20the%20undermining%20of%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20or%20it%20may%20not%20even%20be%20a%20corollary%2C%20it%20is%20perhaps%20the%20purpose%20of%20that%20intent%20too%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrecisely.%20Because%20if%20you%20imagine%20a%20democratically%20committed%20party%2C%20it%20is%20a%20party%20that%20will%20accept%20that%20sometimes%20it%20has%20to%20sit%20in%20the%20opposition%2C%20which%20means%20that%20sometimes%20its%20ideology%20will%20not%20form%20the%20policy%20of%20the%20state.%20Say%20a%20Left-socialist%20party%20will%20know%20that%20sometimes%2C%20the%20state%20will%20not%20be%20left%20socialist.%20But%20the%20Hindutva%20ideology%20does%20not%20permit%20that.%20The%20state%20itself%2C%20and%20not%20just%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%2C%20must%20be%20a%20Hindu%20rashtra%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20beyond%20the%20legitimisation%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20talked%20about%2C%20you%20also%20say%20that%20this%20assault%20on%20democracy%20was%20corroborated%20and%20in%20a%20sense%20enhanced%20by%20the%20way%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20political%20opposition%20was%20constrained%20especially%20by%20targeting%20the%20offices%20and%20institutions%20in%20which%20it%20still%20held%20sway%2C%20such%20as%20the%20upper%20chamber%20in%20the%20federal%20Parliament%2C%20state%20governments%20that%20it%20controls%20and%20the%20office%20of%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%E2%80%9D.%20I%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Epresume%20you%20could%20add%20to%20that%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20own%20failure%20to%20resist%20or%20at%20least%20effectively%20fight%20back%20against%20what%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20doing.%20So%2C%20not%20just%20the%20weakening%20of%20the%20opposition%20but%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20resist%20has%20in%20a%20way%20enhanced%20and%20corroborated%20this%20attack%20and%20assault%20on%20democracy.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20think%20we%20need%20to%20make%20a%20distinction%20here%20between%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20opposition.%20I%20think%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20main%20if%20not%20the%20sole%20fight%20back%20against%20the%20Modi%20regime%20has%20come%20from%20parts%20of%20the%20opposition.%20The%20regional%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20in%20Bengal%2C%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20or%20at%20least%20part%20of%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20now%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20and%20some%20of%20the%20Southern%20parties%2C%20especially%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20They%E2%80%99ve%20been%20very%20valiant%20because%20for%20them%2C%20they%20know%20the%20question%20is%20existential.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20all%20the%20institutions%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20state%20have%20rolled%20over%2C%20including%20the%20courts%20have%20sort%20of%20held%20back%E2%80%A6%20the%20opposition%2C%20the%20regional%20parties%20have%20put%20up%20a%20very%20valiant%20fight%20at%20a%20huge%20personal%20and%20political%20cost%20to%20themselves.%20The%20main%20failure%20of%20the%20opposition%20has%20been%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20main%20opposition%20party%2C%20the%20Congress%20and%20its%20failure%20has%20partly%20been%20the%20dysfunction%20within%20the%20party%20of%20taking%20years%E2%80%A6%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20cost%20India%20dearly%20of%20figuring%20out%20its%20own%20leadership%20and%20not%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etaking%20the%20leadership%20to%20secure%20the%20opposition%20unity%20that%20is%20completely%20%3Cem%3Esine%20qua%20non%3C%2Fem%3E%20(an%20essential%20condition)%20in%20a%20situation%20like%20this.%20If%20you%20have%20to%20fight%20a%20hegemonic%20party%2C%20the%20main%20opposition%20party%20has%20to%20show%20magnanimity%2C%20has%20to%20show%20alacrity.%20This%20should%20have%20happened%20in%202019%2C%20not%20in%202023.%20So%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20is%20where%20the%20failure%20has%20been%20and%20I%20think%20if%20the%20Congress%20had%20acted%20and%20behaved%20differently%2C%20the%20story%20of%20India%20would%20have%20been%20quite%20different%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20is%20where%20the%20crisis%20in%20Congress%20becomes%20in%20fact%20a%20crisis%20for%20Indian%20democracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%3Cspan%3Ebsolutely.%20Which%20is%20why%20what%20happens%20within%20the%20party%20is%20not%20just%20a%20personal%20business%20of%20the%20party.%20As%20democratic%20citizens%2C%20we%20all%20should%20care%20about%20the%20health%20of%20our%20parties%2C%20especially%20the%20opposition%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F08195755%2FFvdM0YTWwAASRHL.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F08195755%2FFvdM0YTWwAASRHL.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F08195755%2FFvdM0YTWwAASRHL-300x151.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F08195755%2FFvdM0YTWwAASRHL-1024x515.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-652209%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22604%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMallikarjun%20Kharge%2C%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20and%20Rahul%20Gandhi.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40INCIndia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinally%2C%20there%20are%20what%20you%20call%20design%20flaws%20in%20the%20constitution%20which%20have%20permitted%20the%20constitution%20to%20be%20killed%20with%20a%20thousand%20cuts.%20What%20are%20the%20sort%20of%20design%20flaws%20you%20have%20in%20mind%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20constitution%20is%20perfect%20and%20every%20constitution%20is%20a%20product%20of%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etime.%20We%20have%20a%20very%20good%20constitution%20on%20the%20whole%2C%20but%20there%20are%20serious%20shortcomings.%20I%20think%20the%20most%20important%20design%20flaw%20in%20our%20constitution%20is%20the%20retention%20of%20centrally%20appointed%20g%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eovernors%20in%20states%20and%20a%20relatively%20centralised%20system%20of%20federalism%20where%20states%20have%20limited%20rights%20and%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20how%20the%20governors%20have%20been%20weaponised%20in%20an%20unprecedented%20manner%20under%20this%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20is%20an%20inadequate%20protection%20of%20opposition%20rights.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20constitutionalised%20office%20of%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20opposition%20days%20in%20parliament%2C%20where%20the%20opposition%20once%20a%20week%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Econtrols%20the%20agenda%20of%20parliament.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20minimum%20number%20of%20days%20that%20parliament%20must%20sit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20constitution%20also%20delegated%20to%20parliament%20to%20decide%20how%20its%20guarantor%20branch%20institutions%20will%20be%20peopled.%20But%20parliament%20has%20not%20done%20that%2C%20which%20gives%20the%20executive%20the%20power%20to%20appoint%20all%20sorts%20of%20officers.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20the%20fight%20over%20the%20election%20commission%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20So%20these%20are%20just%20the%20aspects%20of%20the%20constitution%20where%20there%20was%20too%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emuch%20trust%20in%20the%20executive.%20I%20think%20constitutions%20framed%20with%20a%20Nehru%20or%20Mandela%20in%20mind%20can%20sometimes%20be%20myopic%20because%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20about%20life%20after%20their%20Nehru%20and%20Mandela%20and%20there%20are%20similar%20shortcomings%20in%20the%20South%20African%20constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20I%20put%20it%20like%20this%2C%20if%20you%20design%20a%20constitution%20with%20Nehru%20and%20Mandela%20in%20mind%20you%20aren%E2%80%99t%20envisaging%20the%20possibility%20that%20people%20of%20lesser%20calibre%2C%20people%20whose%20intentions%20may%20not%20be%20so%20honourable%2C%20could%20one%20day%20sit%20in%20the%20same%20powerful%20seats%20that%20these%20men%20have%20sat%20in.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfailure%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20constitution%20not%20to%20envisage%20how%20vile%20men%20can%20be.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbsolutely%2C%20and%20that%20there%20will%20be%20an%20Indira%20Gandhi%20or%20a%20Jacob%20Zumo%20or%20a%20Narendra%20Modi%20who%20will%20occupy%20the%20same%20office%20and%20who%20will%20not%20have%20that%20same%20commitment%20to%20democracy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20Professor%20Khaitan%2C%20you%20make%20one%20more%20point%20about%20the%20first%20Modi%20government.%20You%20say%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20systematicity%20of%20its%20assaults%20on%20all%20accountability-seeking%20mechanisms%20made%20it%20different%20from%20previous%20governments%20which%20had%20all%20been%20constitutionally%20naughty%20every%20now%20and%20then.%20The%20subtlety%20and%20incrementalism%20of%20its%20assaults%20distinguished%20it%20from%20direct%20assaults%20and%20constitutionalism%20during%20the%20emergency.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20has%20the%20Modi%20government%20placed%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%20in%20greater%20peril%20than%20any%20other%20earlier%20government%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20a%20tough%20question%20to%20answer.%20The%20reasons%20why%20Indira%20Gandhi%20ended%20the%20emergency%20and%20called%20for%20elections%20remain%20mysterious.%20There%20was%20no%20compulsion.%20Her%20hand%20was%20certainly%20not%20forced%2C%20there%20was%20no%20external%20force%20that%20made%20her%20do%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat.%20She%20could%20have%20easily%20remained%20in%20power%20for%20the%20next%20decade%20or%20so.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20that%20sense%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20elections%20will%20happen%20and%20the%20opposition%20%E2%80%93%20howsoever%20minuscule%20%E2%80%93%20has%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Echance%20to%20perhaps%20at%20least%20fight%20and%20come%20to%20power%2C%20Indian%20democracy%20is%20in%20a%20better%20state%20than%20under%20the%20Emergency.%20It%20is%20in%20a%20worse%20state%20than%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20regime%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20we%20sleepwalked%20into%20authoritarianism%20because%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20danger%20our%20democracy%20and%20our%20constitution%20are%20in.%20And%20that%20is%20what%20makes%20this%20regime%20much%20more%20dangerous%20because%20the%20kind%20of%20urgency%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20sense%20of%20siege%20that%20democracy%20is%20under%20is%20absent%2C%20which%20means%20that%20the%20mobilisation%20and%20the%20fightback%20have%20not%20been%20of%20the%20same%20quality%20as%20they%20were%20under%20the%20Emergency.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%20when%20you%20say%20and%20I%20think%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%20correctly%20%E2%80%9Cwe%E2%80%99ve%20sleepwalked%20into%20authoritarianism%E2%80%9D%20is%20that%20the%20people%20of%20India%20or%20maybe%20the%20institutions%20of%20India%20or%20maybe%20the%20opposition%20that%20is%20the%20most%20important%20political%20opposition%20to%20the%20government%2C%20none%20of%20these%20three%20categories%20were%20aware%20of%20what%20was%20happening%20realised%20what%20was%20happening%20and%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20it%20was%20happening.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20they%20had%20their%20eyes%20shut.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20that%20is%20indeed%20the%20case%20but%20this%20is%20also%20harder%20to%20see.%20It%E2%80%99s%20just%20that%20the%20autocrats%20of%20today%20are%20much%20smarter%20and%20to%20some%20extent%20lack%20of%20constitutional%20literacy%20is%20also%20to%20be%20blamed.%20When%20we%20equate%20democracy%20with%20elections%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eforget%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20else%20that%20goes%20into%20designing%20a%20democracy%2C%20the%20second%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20the%20third%20dimension%20that%20I%20talked%20about%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20harder%20to%20see%20when%20elections%20are%20still%20happening%2C%20that%20democracy%20might%20be%20under%20threat.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsolutely.%20But%20before%20I%20turn%20to%20the%20second%20Modi%20government%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20interesting%20thought%20that%20will%20perhaps%20have%20crystallised%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20audience.%20The%20Modi%20government%202014-19%20is%20guilty%20of%20killing%20the%20constitution%20with%20a%20thousand%20cuts.%20But%20equally%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20was%20asleep%20and%20let%20it%20happen%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAsleep%20and%20let%20it%20happen%20and%20I%20would%20say%20perhaps%20also%20complicit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBecause%20they%20were%20asleep%20or%20because%20they%20were%20actually%20helping%20as%20well%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20huge%20swathes%20of%20the%20state%20machinery%20%E2%80%93%20the%20bureaucracy%2C%20people%20in%20institutions%20of%20power%20%E2%80%93%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20must%20know%20what%E2%80%99s%20going%20on.%20And%20%5Bthey%5D%20either%20allowed%20it%20to%20happen%20or%20become%20scared%20and%20let%20it%20happen%20or%20wanted%20it%20to%20happen%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20happened%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20we%20know.%20We%20can%E2%80%99t%20get%20into%20their%20minds.%20But%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20did%20not%20stand%20up%20for%20the%20constitution%2C%20I%20think%20is%20a%20huge%20indictment%20and%20I%20think%20history%20will%20judge%20these%20people%20very%20harshly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20again%20to%20put%20it%20in%20colloquial%20language%2C%20what%20Mr%20Modi%20has%20done%20in%20the%20last%20ten%20years%20to%20our%20constitution%20and%20our%20democracy%20is%20%E2%80%93%20if%20I%20can%20use%20that%20colloquial%20word%20%E2%80%93%20hateful.%20But%20equally%20what%20is%20hateful%20is%20that%20some%20of%20us%20were%20asleep%20and%20others%20because%20they%20allowed%20it%20to%20happen%20were%20complicit.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20they%20are%20also%20to%20some%20extent%20hateful%20in%20their%20either%20lack%20of%20response%20or%20in%20their%20complicity.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrecisely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOkay%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20then%20at%20this%20point%20Professor%20Khaitan%20turned%20to%20the%20second%20Modi%20government.%20I%E2%80%99m%20going%20to%20quote%20something%20you%20wrote%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%20and%20ask%20whether%20you%20still%20stand%20by%20it%20or%20whether%20the%20situation%20has%20gotten%20much%20worse%20in%20the%20two-three%20years%20since.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20the%20sentence.%20You%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CSince%20its%20resounding%20victory%20in%20the%202019%20general%20elections%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20appears%20to%20have%20moved%20into%20consolidation%20mode.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHas%20it%20simply%20consolidated%3F%20Or%20when%20you%20look%20back%2C%20has%20it%20gone%20much%20beyond%20the%20consolidation%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20I%20wrote%20that%20sentence%20shortly%20after%20the%202019%20elections%20when%20the%20new%20government%20had%20taken%20office%20and%20what%20I%20underestimated%20and%20what%20I%20did%20not%20see%20then%20was%20just%20how%20important%20the%20Hindu%20rashtra%20agenda%20will%20become%20to%20the%20second%20regime.%20So%20the%20victory%20in%202019%20gave%20a%20swagger%20to%20the%20government%2C%20it%20became%20overconfident%20and%20it%20decided%20that%20the%20subtle%20incremental%20cautious%20step-by-step%20agenda%20was%20perhaps%20unnecessary.%20It%20could%20do%20things%20in%20a%20more%20full-frontal%20way.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20we%20immediately%20saw%20the%20removal%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20we%20saw%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20being%20enacted%2C%20we%20saw%20the%20farm%20Bills%20being%20pushed%20through%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20brazenness%20that%20was%20not%20there%20in%20the%20first%20regime%20suddenly%20became%20visible.%20And%20I%20had%20underestimated%20when%20I%20said%20consolidation%E2%80%A6%20and%20by%20the%20way%2C%20this%20hurt%20the%20regime.%20Because%20with%20the%20kind%20of%20mobilization%20for%20example%20that%20we%20saw%20against%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20with%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20marching%20across%20India%20and%20if%20the%20pandemic%20had%20not%20happened%2C%20that%20would%20have%20continued%20for%20much%20longer%20%E2%80%93%20or%20the%20kind%20of%20opposition%20to%20the%20farm%20Bills%2C%20we%20did%20not%20see%20in%20the%20first%20regime.%20So%2C%20an%20overconfident%20regime%20also%20painted%20a%20much%20clearer%20target%20than%20the%20incremental%20%5Bway%20would%20have%5D.%20So%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20caution%20was%20thrown%20to%20the%20wind%20by%20the%20second%20regime.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F10230450%2FCAA-act-protest.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F10230450%2FCAA-act-protest.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F10230450%2FCAA-act-protest-300x128.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F10230450%2FCAA-act-protest-1024x435.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-426650%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22510%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPeople%20protest%20the%20Citizenship%20(Amendment)%20Act%20in%20Delhi.%20Photo%3A%20Naomi%20Barton%2FThe%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20yes%20there%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Econsolidation%20in%20the%20way%20that%20we%20have%20seen%20with%20the%20law%20on%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20the%20aggressiveness%20towards%20the%20judiciary%20increased%20manifold%2C%20the%20governors%20became%20a%20lot%20more%20brazen.%20All%20of%20the%20things%20that%20were%20happening%20more%20subtly%E2%80%A6%20certainly%2C%20they%20stepped%20on%20the%20accelerator.%20But%20the%20Hindutva%20agenda%2C%20you%20know%20the%20entire%20point%20of%20Hindutva%20is%20symbolism.%20The%20Hindu%20rashtra%20is%20a%20symbolic%20ideal.%20Incrementalism%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20work%20there%20step%20by%20step%2C%20%3Cem%3Esotto%20voce%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Esubtlety%20does%20not%20work%20there.%20The%20point%20is%20to%20shout%20from%20the%20rooftops%20and%20that%20is%20what%20is%20a%20defining%20feature%20of%20the%20second%20regime%20in%20my%20view.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20ask%20you%20a%20specific%20question%20about%20Hindutva%20and%20the%20Hindu%20rashtra.%20Clearly%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20acquired%20a%20much%20sharper%20cultural%20focus%20in%20Modi%202%20than%20in%20Modi%201.%20I%E2%80%99m%20referring%20to%20things%20like%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20the%20handling%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20sengol%20in%20Parliament%2C%20the%20persecution%20of%20Muslims%20in%20UP%20and%20Nuh%20and%20of%20course%20using%20the%20name%20Bharat%20in%20place%20of%20India.%20But%20is%20this%20simply%2C%20all%20taken%20together%2C%20undermining%20our%20democracy%20or%20is%20it%20also%20changing%20the%20character%20of%20the%20country%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20defining%20or%20redefining%20who%20we%20are%20as%20a%20people%2C%20so%20it%E2%80%99s%20fundamental.%20You%20can%20say%20what%20you%20will%20about%20the%20RSS%2C%20the%20one%20thing%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20lack%20is%20patience.%20This%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebeen%20a%20single-minded%20focused%20agenda%20of%20the%20RSS%20for%20decades%20and%20finally%20come%20to%20fruition.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20think%20effectively%2C%20I%20would%20say%20we%20are%20very%20close%20to%20if%20not%20already%20achieved%20Hindu%20rashtra%20%E2%80%93%20except%20for%20the%20formal%20declaration%2C%20that%20might%20be%20waiting.%20The%20second-class%20citizenship%20of%20non-Hindus%20is%20now%20enshrined%20in%20our%20laws%20like%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emob%20violence%20we%20see%20across%20the%20country.%20What%20we%20have%20not%20seen%20is%20a%20clear%20ideological%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ealternative%20to%20Hindutva.%20The%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Yatra%20was%20important%20in%20trying%20to%20get%20that%20message%20across%20through%20action.%20But%20actions%20have%20to%20be%20matched%20by%20words%20and%20the%20BJP%20is%20a%20master%20in%20coining%20memorable%20phrases.%20You%20know%2C%20the%20Congress%20could%20have%20thought%20about%20an%20alternative%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EHindustaniat%3C%2Fem%3E%20right%2C%20which%20could%20have%20been%20imbued%20with%20ideas%20of%20a%20tolerance%20for%20pluralism%2C%20a%20tolerance%20for%20difference%2C%20of%20being%20happy%20with%20difference%20around%20you.%20We%20have%20not%20seen%20that%20counter%2C%20%5Banother%5D%20way%20to%20belong%20%5Bthat%20answers%20the%20question%2C%5D%20what%20does%20it%20mean%20to%20be%20an%20Indian%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuite%20right.%20Once%20again%2C%20the%20inability%20of%20the%20opposition%20to%20counter%20the%20message%20of%20Hindutva%20with%20an%20alternative%20paradigm%20of%20its%20own%20has%20assisted%20Hindutva%20in%20changing%20what%20I%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cstrong%3Ecall%20the%20character%20of%20the%20country%20and%20what%20you%20call%20redefining%20us%20as%20the%20sort%20of%20people%20we%20are.%20A%20second%20key%20aspect%20of%20Modi%202%20is%20questions%20that%20are%20raised%20by%20people%20like%20the%20vice%20president%20whether%20there%20is%20a%20basic%20structure%20to%20the%20constitution%20and%20the%20whole%20debate%20about%20whether%20we%20need%20a%20new%20constitution.%20That%20debate%20is%20certainly%20flowing%20not%20subterraneously%20but%20fairly%20at%20the%20surface%20at%20the%20moment.%20Do%20you%20see%20this%20again%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20democracy%20or%20is%20this%20questioning%20of%20the%20constitution%20being%20wrongly%20understood%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20we%20should%20notice%20a%20mode%20in%20which%20this%20government%20functions.%20It%20has%20a%20very%20radical%20agenda%20to%20change%20not%20just%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20but%20the%20Indian%20people.%20And%20the%20way%20it%20works%20is%2C%20its%20most%20radical%20ideas%20are%20first%20floated%20as%20thought%20balloons%20by%20relative%20outsiders%20with%20plausible%20deniability.%20Then%2C%20that%20agenda%20is%20repeated%20adium%20to%20normalise%20it%20and%20then%20eventually%20enacted.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20this%20with%20simultaneous%20polls%20and%20this%20might%20be%20happening%20%5Bwith%20the%20demand%20for%20a%20new%20constitution%5D.%20So%2C%20I%20think%20we%20are%20currently%20in%20the%20thought%20balloon%20phase%20of%20changing%20or%20replacing%20the%20constitution.%20That%20is%20politically%20risky%20for%20the%20BJP%20because%20India%E2%80%99s%20Dalit%20population%20has%20a%20reverence%20for%20the%20constitution%20because%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20its%20association%20with%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar.%20So%20how%20this%20will%20play%20out%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%20I%20think%20they%E2%80%99re%20gauging%20the%20popular%20reaction%20by%20floating%20the%20ideas%2C%20but%20yes%20if%20they%20do%20decide%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20think%20a%20lot%20will%20turn%20on%20whether%20they%20win%20and%20how%20they%20win%20in%202024.%20If%20they%20win%20big%20and%20if%20they%20think%20they%20can%20take%20that%20political%20risk%20and%20if%20they%20decide%20to%20go%20ahead%2C%20we%20may%20well%20have%20a%20new%20constitution%20and%20it%20will%20remain%20democratic%20by%20the%20way%20%E2%80%93%20but%20democratic%20in%20a%20very%20constrained%20very%20minimalistic%20way%20because%20a%20small%20constrained%20opposition%20that%20allows%20the%20regime%20to%20call%20itself%20democratic%20is%20hugely%20useful%20internationally.%20I%20mean%2C%20in%20that%20legitimising%20role%20that%20the%20label%20democracy%20%5Bprovides%5D.%20But%20yeah%2C%20we%20will%20become%20a%20%E2%80%9Cguided%20democracy%E2%80%9D%20with%20a%20hegemonic%20party%20system.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20at%20the%20moment%20all%20this%20talk%20about%20whether%20there%20is%20a%20basic%20structure%20or%20not%2C%20whether%20we%20need%20a%20new%20constitution%20or%20not%20is%20an%20incipient%20threat.%20Whether%20it%20materializes%20into%20a%20real%20threat%20will%20depend%20critically%20on%20how%20big%20a%20majority%20Mr%20Modi%20can%20win%20in%202024.%20That%E2%80%99s%20another%20reason%20why%20%5Bthe%20BJP%20winning%5D%20300%20plus%20%5Bseats%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%5D%20could%20be%20very%20worrying%20for%20the%20future%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20character%20as%20a%20democracy.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbsolutely.%20And%20I%20suspect%20that%20at%20least%20it%E2%80%99ll%20be%20politically%20wiser%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethem%20instead%20of%20making%20a%20new%20constitution%2C%20to%20do%20something%20like%20the%2042nd%20Amendment%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20in%20effect%20a%20new%20constitution%2C%20but%20done%20not%20as%20a%20constitutional%20replacement%20but%20through%20the%20process%20of%20amendment%20%E2%80%93%20because%20you%20can%20still%20pay%20lip%20service%20to%20Dr%20Ambedkar%20and%20still%20move%20to%20a%20presidential%20system%20get%20rid%20of%20federalism%20and%20do%20all%20the%20other%20things%20and%20enshrine%20Hindu%20rashtra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20the%20interesting%20thing%20by%20the%20way%20is%20this%20talk%20about%20moving%20the%20system%20from%20a%20parliamentary%20to%20a%20presidential%20was%20also%20something%20that%20was%20discussed%20during%20the%20emergency%20if%20I%20recall%20correctly%20and%20correct%20me%20if%20I%E2%80%99m%20wrong.%20B.K.%20Nehru%20wrote%20a%20paper%20on%20the%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Esubject%20advocating%20a%20switch%20from%20a%20parliamentary%20to%20a%20presidential%20democracy%20and%20he%20was%20incidentally%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20uncle%20or%20first%20cousin.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20came%20up%20in%20the%20Vajpayee%20regime%2C%20if%20you%20recall.%20The%20Constitution%20Review%20Committee%20was%20set%20up%20precisely%20for%20this%20task%20and%20it%20was%20President%20K.R.%20Narayanan%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20%E2%80%93%20%5Basking%5D%20whether%20the%20constitution%20has%20failed%20us%20or%20have%20we%20failed%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20which%20killed%20that%20idea%2C%20because%20that%20was%20a%20constitutionally%20civil%20regime.%20And%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eway%2C%20the%20presidential%20system%20is%20every%20elected%20autocrat%E2%80%99s%20wet%20dream.%20That%20is%20what%20they%20all%20want.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsolutely.%20Now%2C%20a%20third%20aspect%20of%20Modi%202%20are%20attempts%20to%20downsize%20or%20clip%20the%20wings%20of%20established%20institutions%20and%20political%20entities.%20I%E2%80%99m%20referring%20to%20the%20election%20commission%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20referring%20to%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20Delhi%20government%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20referring%20even%20to%20this%20incipient%20debate%20now%20we%20have%20a%20formal%20committee%20investigating%20the%20matter%20whether%20we%20should%20have%20simultaneous%20elections%20or%20not%20because%20if%20they%20happen%20it%20will%20certainly%20ensure%20that%20the%20autonomy%20of%20state%20legislatures%20will%20be%20curtailed%20so%20they%20can%20synchronize%20with%20the%20national%20legislature.%20Again%2C%20how%20serious%20is%20all%20of%20this%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20undermining%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EO%3Cspan%3Eh%2C%20this%20is%20hugely%20serious.%20I%20think%20in%20some%20ways%20they%20have%20already%20replaced%20the%20constitution%20and%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20Hindu%20rashtra%20is%20already%20here%20%E2%80%93%20the%20formal%20announcement%20is%20awaited.%20These%20changes%20will%20entrench%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20will%20realise%20the%2050-year%20reign%20that%20Amit%20Shah%20dreams%20of.%20A%20brave%20judiciary%2C%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efunctional%20judiciary%2C%20a%20judiciary%20that%20saw%20the%20dangers%20and%20did%20not%20sit%20on%20cases%20for%20years%20could%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20nipped%20it%20in%20the%20bud%20but%20now%20much%20water%20has%20flown%20and%20now%20the%20judiciary%20itself%20is%20scared%20or%20compromised%20or%20unwilling%20to%20act%20for%20reasons%20that%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand.%20All%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20these%20things%20will%20fundamentally%20change%20all%20the%20accountability%20mechanisms%3B%20the%20most%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Edangerous%20branch%20has%20become%20even%20more%20dangerous.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20which%20case%2C%20one%20last%20question.%20Has%20the%20peril%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%20increased%20or%20at%20least%20become%20more%20widespread%20and%20comprehensive%20and%20not%20limited%20just%20to%20a%20few%20areas%20under%20the%20second%20Modi%20government%3F%20Or%20would%20that%20be%20an%20exaggeration%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EN%3Cspan%3Eo%2C%20it%20has%20increased%20compared%20to%20the%20first%20government.%20I%20think%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20swagger%20after%20the%202019%20elections%20has%20made%20it%20a%20lot%20less%20cautious%20but%20the%20mask%20has%20also%20slipped.%20This%20is%20perhaps%20a%20hopeful%20optimistic%20note.%20The%20CAA%20protests%20changed%20the%20international%20at%20least%20complicated%20the%20international%20coverage%20of%20the%20regime.%