%3B%20Sinwar%20wrote%20in%20Hebrew%2C%20according%20to%20former%20National%20Security%20Adviser%20Meir%20Ben-Shabbat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20long%20before%2C%20the%20Hamas%20chief%20had%20said%20something%20similar%20to%20an%20Italian%20journalist%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20war%20anymore.%20I%20want%20a%20ceasefire.%26quot%3B%20His%20ambition%20for%20the%20impoverished%20Palestinian%20coastal%20strip%3F%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20be%20like%20Singapore%2C%20like%20Dubai.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20wake%20of%20Hamas's%20long-planned%20and%20brutal%20Oct.%207%20assault%20on%20Israel%2C%20the%20Israeli%20security%20establishment%20is%20looking%20back%20on%20his%20words%20in%20a%20new%20light%3A%20as%20part%20of%20an%20effort%20to%20create%20the%20illusion%20that%20Hamas%2C%20considered%20a%20terrorist%20group%20by%20the%20US%20and%20European%20Union%2C%20was%20limiting%20its%20embrace%20of%20violence%20to%20focus%20on%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20officials%20now%20acknowledge%20that%20a%20sense%20of%20complacency%20had%20set%20in%20around%20Hamas.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20military%20had%20greatly%20reduced%20its%20surveillance%20of%20the%20Gaza%20border%20fence%2C%20relying%20on%20electronic%20sensors%20and%20transferring%20troops%20out%20of%20the%20area%20to%20guard%20settlements%20in%20the%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Israeli%20analyst%20Chen%20Artzi%20Sror%20wrote%20recently%20in%20the%20Yedioth%20Ahronoth%20newspaper%2C%20ambitious%20military%20intelligence%20analysts%20preferred%20to%20focus%20on%20Iran%20and%20Syria%20because%20working%20on%20Palestinian%20issues%20was%20not%20considered%20of%20existential%20importance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20overarching%20sentiment%20was%20that%20Hamas%20had%20been%20deterred%2C%20and%20that%20the%20real%20challenges%20lay%20further%20afield.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSinwar%20read%20the%20Israeli%20consciousness%20very%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michael%20Milshtein%2C%20former%20head%20of%20Palestinian%20research%20for%20the%20military's%20intelligence%20department.%20%26quot%3BHe%20wanted%20Israel%20to%20believe%20that%20Hamas%20was%20concentrating%20on%20stability%20in%20Gaza%2C%20promoting%20civil%20affairs.%20He%20planted%20this%20wrong%20idea%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20Israelis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20as%20the%20Israeli%20military%20reduces%20much%20of%20Gaza%20to%20rubble%20in%20its%20mission%20to%20destroy%20Hamas%2C%20killing%20more%20than%2011%2C000%20people%20in%20the%20process%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Hamas-run%20health%20ministry%2C%20Sinwar%20is%20emerging%20as%20the%20assault's%20mastermind.%20He's%20the%20top%20target%20for%20assassination%2C%20assumed%20to%20be%20hiding%20deep%20in%20a%20Gaza%20tunnel%2C%20%26quot%3Blike%20a%20little%20Hitler%20in%20a%20bunker%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Netanyahu%20put%20it%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20Oct.%207%20attacks%20remake%20regional%20-%20even%20global%20-%20politics%2C%20raising%20a%20risk%20of%20broader%20war%2C%20it's%20notable%20that%20the%20dynamic%20that%20gave%20rise%20to%20it%20is%20one%20of%20intimate%20enemies.%20Sinwar%20and%20the%20Israelis%20have%20been%20watching%20and%20analyzing%20one%20another%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20a%20poor%20neighborhood%20of%20the%20southern%20Gaza%20town%20of%20Khan%20Younis%2C%20Sinwar%2C%2061%2C%20helped%20found%20Hamas's%20military%20wing%20in%20the%20late%201980s%20as%20the%20first%20Palestinian%20uprising%20was%20underway.%20He%20later%20took%20on%20the%20task%20of%20rooting%20out%20Palestinian%20collaborators%20with%20Israel%2C%20and%20was%20responsible%20for%20killing%20four%20of%20them.%20Israeli%20military%20authorities%2C%20at%20the%20time%20still%20operating%20inside%20Gaza%2C%20sentenced%20him%20to%20life%20in%20prison%20in%201989.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBehind%20bars%2C%20Sinwar%20achieved%20deep%20fluency%20in%20Hebrew%20and%20Israeli%20society%2C%20regularly%20reading%20newspapers%20along%20with%20the%20biographies%20of%20key%20Israeli%20figures.%20He%20also%20became%20the%20uncontested%20leader%20of%20Hamas%20prisoners.%20According%20to%20Israeli%20officials%20and%20a%20former%20Hamas%20activist%2C%20while%20in%20prison%20he%20continued%20to%20have%20collaborators%20killed%20-%20including%20one%20he%20personally%20beheaded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20describe%20him%20as%20a%20cold-blooded%2C%20magnetic%20leader%3B%20a%20compact%2C%20sinewy%20man%20whose%20close-cropped%20hair%20and%20beard%20have%20by%20now%20mostly%20turned%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20while%20in%20prison%2C%20Sinwar%20began%20experiencing%20headaches%20and%20blurred%20vision.%20He%20was%20taken%20to%20the%20Soroka%20Medical%20Center%20in%20Beersheba%20where%20a%20surgeon%20removed%20a%20brain%20tumor%2C%20saving%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetty%20Lahat%2C%20the%20prison%20system's%20intelligence%20chief%20at%20the%20time%2C%20said%20in%20a%20TV%20documentary%20that%20she%20tried%20to%20use%20that%20event%20to%20recruit%20him%20as%20an%20agent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20said%2C%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20saved%20your%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%20I%20could%20turn%20him%20into%20one%20of%20ours%2C%20but%20he%20wasn't%20interested.%20He%20kept%20talking%20about%20the%20day%20he%20would%20be%20released.%20I%20told%20him%20you're%20never%20getting%20out.%20He%20said%20there's%20a%20date%3A%20God%20knows%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20date.%20It%20was%20Oct.%2018%2C%202011%2C%20when%20Israel%20exchanged%20more%20than%201%2C000%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20for%20an%20Israeli%20soldier%20held%20by%20Hamas%2C%20Gilad%20Shalit.%20Among%20those%20released%20-%20and%20the%20man%20who%20drew%20up%20the%20list%20-%20was%20Sinwar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20he'd%20killed%20fellow%20Palestinians%20and%20not%20Israelis%2C%20and%20was%20no%20longer%20young%2C%20some%20Israeli%20officials%20didn't%20object%20to%20his%20being%20on%20the%20list.%20Others%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20talk%20of%20how%20he%20was%20not%20a%20threat%2C%26quot%3B%20recalled%20Milshtein%2C%20the%20former%20intelligence%20officer.%20%26quot%3BHe%20doesn't%20want%20to%20return%20to%20dangerous%20activity%2C%20he's%20forgotten%20how%20to%20plan%20a%20terror%20attack.%20I%20tried%20to%20tell%20them%20they%20were%20wrong.%20Hamas%20is%20a%20mission%20for%20your%20whole%20life.%20It%20took%20him%20only%20a%20week%20to%20return%20to%20his%20connections%20and%20activities.%20Today%2C%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%20is%20Sinwar.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20rejoined%20Hamas%20at%20a%20senior%20level%20and%20by%202017%20had%20been%20elected%20the%20group's%20leader%20for%20all%20of%20Gaza%2C%20replacing%20Ismail%20Haniyeh%2C%20who%20was%20sent%20to%20Qatar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHamas%20and%20Sinwar%20misled%20Israel%20and%20made%20it%20think%20war%20wasn't%20an%20option%20for%20Hamas%2C%26quot%3B%20Akram%20Atallah%2C%20a%20Gaza-based%20columnist%20for%20the%20West%20Bank%20newspaper%20Al%20Ayyam%2C%20said%20by%20phone.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20sophisticated%20misinformation%20campaign%20deceiving%20Israel%20into%20believing%20they%20were%20seeking%20peace%2C%20workers%2C%20and%20economic%20life%20for%20Gaza%20residents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20October%20attack%2C%20a%20senior%20Hamas%20official%2C%20Ali%20Baraka%2C%20told%20the%20Russian%20state%20channel%20RT%20something%20similar%20-%20that%20the%20group%20had%20prepared%20for%20Oct.%207%20for%20two%20years%20while%20fooling%20Israel%20into%20thinking%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bbusy%20governing%20Gaza.%26quot%3B%20Planning%20encompassed%20not%20only%20the%20attack%2C%20but%20also%20how%20Hamas%20would%20rule%20in%20its%20aftermath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20subject%20of%20a%202021%20conference%20in%20Gaza%20entitled%20%26quot%3BThe%20Promise%20of%20the%20End%20