ovember%202022)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20main%20country-based%20case%20studies%20identified%20in%20Svitych%E2%80%99s%20thesis%20remains%20restricted%20to%20four%20OECD%20countries%2C%20namely%20Hungary%2C%20Australia%2C%20France%2C%20and%20South%20Korea%2C%20the%20analytical%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrill.com%2Fdisplay%2Ftitle%2F62356%3Flanguage%3Den%5C%22%3Etheoretical%20contributions%20from%20his%20book%E2%80%99s%20thesis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20use%20of%20Polanyi%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20establish%20an%20inextricable%20link%20between%20discontented%20experiments%20of%20free%20market%20reforms%2C%20declining%20state%20legitimacy%2C%20and%20identity-based%20mobilisation%2C%20which%20has%20been%20defining%20the%20nature%20of%20geopolitics%20across%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20studies%20on%20the%20contested%20phenomenon%20of%20populism%2C%20including%20the%20book%20titled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.taylorfrancis.com%2Fbooks%2Fmono%2F10.4324%2F9781003298694%2Fstrongmen-saviours-deepanshu-mohan-abhinav-padmanabhan%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EStrongmen%20Saviours%E2%80%A6%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20tried%20to%20study%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdemand%20side%E2%80%9D%20or%20the%20%E2%80%9Csupply%20side%E2%80%9D%20reasons%20or%20causes%20for%20the%20electoral%20success%20of%20neo-nationalist%20leaders%2C%20and%20their%20respective%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20neo-nationalism%20across%20nations%20from%20both%20the%20developed%20Global%20North%20(from%20the%20US%20to%20France)%20and%20developing%20Global%20South%20(from%20India%20to%20Brazil%20to%20Turkey)%20is%20observed%20in%20different%20contexts.%20These%20are%20rising%20unemployment%2C%20inequality%2C%20weakening%20labour%20power%2C%20an%20inefficient%20functioning%20of%20a%20corrupt%20bureaucratic%20state%2C%20triggering%20anti-establishment%20sentiments%2C%20and%20the%20role%20of%20cultural%20grievances%2C%20perceived%20ethnic%20threat%2C%20increase%20in%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConceptualising%20populism%20as%20a%20thin-centered%20ideology%20driven%20by%20nationalist%20appeals%20allows%20to%20trace%20such%20important%20ideological%20shifts%2C%20according%20to%20Svitych.%20Labelling%20these%20shifts%20as%20%E2%80%9Cradical%20right%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cright-wing%20populism%E2%80%9D%20conceptually%20offers%20a%20limiting%20view.%20There%20are%20more%20underlying%20factors%20shaping%20these%20shifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOleksandr%20interprets%20neo-nationalism%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csocietal%20reaction%20against%20the%20capital%20state%20%E2%80%93%20a%20polity%20safeguarding%20the%20market%20order%20under%20the%20auspices%20of%20neoliberal%20globalisation%2C%20whereby%2C%20three%20clusters%20of%20institutional%20developments%20exhibit%20this%20uncoupling%20of%20the%20state%20from%20society%3A%20privatisation%20and%20individuation%20of%20the%20provisions%20for%20health%2C%20education%2C%20and%20welfare%3B%20precarisation%20of%20work%20and%20the%20weakening%20power%20of%20labour%3B%20and%20financialisation%20of%20the%20economy%20that%20redistributed%20wealth%20to%20the%20top%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%E2%80%99s%20thesis%20makes%20an%20important%20observation%20in%20the%20context%20of%20seeing%20the%20rise%20of%20neo-nationalism%2Fpopulism%20as%20a%20process%20of%20transforming%20the%20%E2%80%98welfare%20state%E2%80%99%20into%20a%20%E2%80%98new%20capital%20state%E2%80%99.%20The%20author%20defines%20%E2%80%98new%20capital%20state%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20latest%20paradigm%20of%20state%20development%2C%20distinguished%20by%20intensive%20commodification%20that%20favours%20the%20interests%20of%20capital%20over%20public%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20is%20a%20slight%20disagreement%20with%20author%20Svitych.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fthe-flipside-of-neo-nationalism%5C%22%3EThe%20Flipside%20of%20Neo-Nationalism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20observation%20might%20be%20partially%20true%20for%20most%20of%20the%20OECD-based%20case%20studies%20cited%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrill.com%2Fdisplay%2Ftitle%2F62356%3Flanguage%3Den%5C%22%3ESvitych%20in%20his%20book%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Ebut%20in%20context%20of%20scenarios%20emerging%20from%20different%20countries%20of%20the%20developing%20global%20South%2C%20say%2C%20India%20or%20Turkey%2C%20which%20have%20seen%20their%20own%20tryst%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20right-wing%20populism%2C%20they%20provide%20a%20slightly%20differed%20%E2%80%98transformation%E2%80%99.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20the%20old-welfare%20state%20has%20not%20necessarily%20given%20way%20to%20a%20new%20capital%20state%20system.%20Moreover%2C%20it%20has%20also%20seen%20a%20%E2%80%98new%20form%20of%20populist-welfarism%E2%80%99%20making%20any%20such%20analysis%20less%20linear%2C%20from%20what%20Svitych%20argues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%20the%20Indian%20context%2C%20under%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20under%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20there%20is%20congruence%20between%20a%20significant%20transformation%20in%20the%20application%20of%20the%20new%20capital%20state%2C%20which%20Oleksandr%20speaks%20of%2C%20and%20the%20redistributive%20welfare%20state.%20In%20this%20scenario%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20own%20name%20and%20central%20government%20funds%20are%20used%20for%20the%20direct%20delivery%20of%20welfare%20services%20(or%20public%20goods)%20amidst%20targeted%20beneficiaries%20and%20the%20poor%20for%20populist-electoral%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20noteworthy%20to%20observe%20how%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20just%20before%20the%20upcoming%20state%20assembly%20elections%2C%20announced%2C%20in%20rallies%20across%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2F5-year-extension-to-pmgkay-an-acknowledgment-of-indias-nutrition-access-crisis%5C%22%3Eextend%20the%20%E2%80%98free-ration%E2%80%99%20PMGKAY%20programme%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20another%20five%20years.%20The%20programme%2C%20introduced%20in%202020%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20lockdown%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2F5-year-extension-to-pmgkay-an-acknowledgment-of-indias-nutrition-access-crisis%5C%22%3Eseeks%20to%20offer%20ration%20to%2080%20crore%20poorer%20beneficiaries%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20India.%20It%20was%20a%20key%20factor%20in%20allowing%20critical%20electoral%20support%20for%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20last%20state%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20missing%20wood%20from%20the%20trees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20set%20of%20key%20points%20deserving%20further%20exploration%20in%20Oleksandr%E2%80%99s%20work%20pertains%20to%20the%20operational%20behavior%20of%20other%20neo-nationalist%20regimes.%20This%20centers%20on%20the%20observed%20%E2%80%98change%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20everyday%20political%20ethics%20embraced%20by%20the%20citizenry%2C%20especially%20those%20in%20unquestioning%2C%20blind%20support%20of%20a%20populist%20leader%20or%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20highlight%20how%20a%20persistent%20rise%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20own%20popularity%20%E2%80%93%20and%20his%20consolidation%20of%20power%20across%20the%20nation%2C%20from%20one%20national%20election%20to%20another%20%E2%80%93%20was%20accentuated%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3Ethe%20emotive%20politics%20of%20%3Cem%3Eandha-vishwas%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20weaponised%20through%20a%20rhetorical%20narrative%20push%2C%20using%20tools%20of%20information%20technology%20and%20state-propagandist%20media.%20This%20could%20be%20understood%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20political%20right%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3EModi-Shah%3C%2Fa%3E%20regime%E2%80%99s%20complex%20experiments%20with%20the%20everyday%20political%20ethics%20of%20being%20built%20around%20the%20tradecraft%20of%20seducing%20the%20emotive%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FPolitics-Ethics-and-Emotions-in-New-India%2FGudavarthy%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032070827%5C%22%3EIn%20his%20recent%20work%20on%20Indian%20neo-nationalism%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fa%3E%20rise%20under%20Modi%2C%20Ajay%20Gudavarthy%20wrote%20about%20an%20interesting%20aspect%2C%20as%20reviewed%20earlier%2C%20of%20viewing%20the%20%E2%80%98emotive%E2%80%99%20influence%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20popularity%20amongst%20the%20larger%20Indian%20electorate%2C%20especially%20the%20Hindi-belt%2C%20despite%20the%20nature%20of%20social%20or%20economic%20issues%20that%20afflict%20the%20same%20majority.%20This%20is%20established%20by%20understanding%20that%20the%20right%20invests%20in%20%3Cem%3Emorality%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20what%20a%20majority%20works%20with%20%3Cem%3Eis%20everyday%20ethics%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3EThe%20Political%20Ethics%20of%20the%20Indian%20Political%20Right%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20that%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Ethe%20everyday%20ethics%20of%20being%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20what%20may%20help%20explain%20the%20average%20Hindu%20voter%E2%80%99s%20motivational%20rationality%20can%20be%20studied%20by%20viewing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Ethe%20application%20of%20%3Cem%3EDharma%2C%20Dharam%2C%20Kama%2C%20Karma%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20way%20these%20influence%20one%E2%80%99s%20daily%20life%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20motivation%20and%20cultural%20propriety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Brahmanical%20cloak%2C%20originally%20intended%20to%20provide%20guidance%2C%20has%20become%20deeply%20politicised%20by%20the%20current%20regime%20led%20by%20Modi-Shah%20and%20%5Bindirectly%5D%20the%20RSS.%20In%20their%20pursuit%20of%20establishing%20a%20Hindu%20Rashtra%2C%20there%20is%20a%20concerted%20effort%20to%20influence%20these%20symbols%20for%20the%20%E2%80%99emotive%20(Hindu)%20majority%E2%80%99%20to%20take%20pride%20in%20themselves%20or%20to%20assert%20majoritarian%20victimhood%2C%20as%20projected%20by%20Modi%20in%20his%20representation%20of%20both%20self%20and%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20role%20of%20Hindutva%20in%20defining%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Enature%20of%20faith%20and%20applied%20religious%20discourse%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20one%20to%20practice%20its%20majoritarian%20belief%20and%20assertion%20by%20%E2%80%98Cleaning%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98teaching%20minorities%20a%20lesson%2C%20%E2%80%98establishing%20masculine%20muscularity%20in%20a%20hyper-nationalist%20wave%E2%80%99%2C%20is%20all%20part%20of%20a%20political%20project%20that%20builds%20itself%20on%20a%20new%20morality%2C%20ethics%20of%20being%20for%20emotions%20(rage%2C%20anger%2C%20violence)%20to%20be%20experienced%20and%20realised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20technology%2C%20conservatism%20in%20belief%20systems%2C%20and%20their%20role%20in%20neo-nationalism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20new%20capital-state%20theory%20put%20forth%20by%20Svitych%2C%20neo-nationalism%20unfolds%20as%20a%20protective%20counter-movement%20against%20the%20erosion%20of%20old%20economic%20and%20social%20structures%2C%20creating%20another%20iteration%20of%20Polanyi%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cdouble-movement%E2%80%9D%20dynamic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20the%20capital-state%2C%20therefore%2C%20and%20the%20subsequent%20economic%2C%20social%2C%20and%20political%20discontent%20gave%20rise%20to%20counter-movements%20of%20both%20the%20Left%20and%20the%20Right%20form%20of%20neo-nationalism%20waves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20surely%20agreement%20here%2C%20and%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20analytical%20observations%20remain%20consistent%20with%20some%20of%20the%20non-western%20%E2%80%98neo-nationalist%E2%80%99%20cases%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeoliberal%2C%20supply-side%20economic%20policies%2C%20which%20accentuate%20inequality%20and%20dismantle%20the%20fundamental%20social%20and%20economic%20protections%20of%20a%20welfarist%20state%2C%20have%2C%20in%20many%20nations%2C%20given%20rise%20to%20or%20produced%20neo-nationalism%20through%20the%20emergence%20of%20the%20new%20capital%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20outcome%20of%20these%20processes%20could%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20strengthening%20of%20ethnic-nationalist%20sources%20of%20collective%20identity%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20Hindutva%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20case%3B%20Orthodox%20Islam%20in%20Turkey%3B%20Evangelical%20Christian%20beliefs%20in%20Brazil%20and%20the%20US%2C%20for%20shaping%20right-wing%20populism%2C%20and%20a%20revival%20of%20civic-based%20values%20to%20reassert%20national%20identity%20through%20a%20class-based%20narrative%2C%20allowing%20for%20left-wing%20populist%20movements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20normative%20axis%20of%20the%20book%20misses%20a%20robust%20critique%20of%20%E2%80%98liberal%20foundations%E2%80%99%20and%20principles%20that%20may%20be%20less%20relevant%20in%20the%20context%20of%20Indian%20polity%20or%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20empirical%20gap%20in%20the%20book%E2%80%99s%20thesis%2C%20which%20stems%20from%20a%20normative%20void%2C%20is%20the%20weak%20link%20established%20between%20the%20actions%20of%20the%20political%20Right%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98narrativizing%E2%80%99%20an%20alternative%20%E2%80%98truth%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20addresses%20the%20emotive%20majority%E2%80%99s%20desire%20to%20immortalise%20acquired%20knowledge%20of%20the%20past%20in%20the%20pursuit%20of%20discovering%20a%20%E2%80%98new%E2%80%99%20truth.%20The%20book%20falls%20short%20in%20fully%20exploring%20this%20dynamic%2C%20particularly%20in%20understanding%20it%20as%20part%20of%20the%20complex%20techno-political%20relationship%20the%20Right%20shares%20with%20contemporary%20tools%20and%20mechanisms%20of%20the%20current%20information%20order%2C%20such%20as%20digital%20technological%20infrastructure%2C%20which%20the%20Right%20effectively%20weaponises%20on%20a%20day-to-day%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Erise%20of%20conservative%20religious-moral%20belief%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20a%20key%20contributing%20factor%20in%20driving%20neo-nationalist%20movements%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20context%20of%20contemporary%20political%20drive%20of%20populism%20in%20developing%20nations%20such%20as%20India%2C%20Turkey%2C%20and%20Brazil.%20The%20normative%20vision%20and%20ideas%20of%20conservative%20ethics%20or%20morality%20are%20channelled%20through%20new%20forms%20of%20symbolism%2C%20manipulated%20through%20media%20and%20information%20flow.%20This%20dynamic%20is%20particularly%20crucial%20for%20the%20Modi-Shah%20double%20engine%20in%20India%2C%20not%20only%20in%20the%20acquisition%20and%20centralisation%20of%20power%20but%20also%20in%20its%20consolidation%20through%20emotive%20narrativisation%20over%20the%20last%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20%E2%80%93%20much%20like%20other%20pillars%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20have%20been%20weaponised%20for%20this%20neo-nationalism%20project%20which%20warrants%20further%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20article%20builds%20the%20thesis%20of%20neo-nationalism%E2%80%99s%20causal%20linkage%2C%20and%20its%20effect%2C%20with%20different%20determining%20factors%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20context%20of%20nations%20identified%20outside%20the%20scope%20of%20Olenksadr%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20four%20selected%20OECD%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700472665000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F09155320%2FIMG_0444.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fhow-neo-nationalism-has-fuelled-the-transformation-of-old-welfare-state-to-new-capital-state%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Oleksandr%20Svitych's%20new%20book%20provides%20an%20empirical%20answer%20to%20this%20question.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fhow-neo-nationalism-has-fuelled-the-transformation-of-old-welfare-state-to-new-capital-state%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22''Great%20Leaders%20Also...''%3A%20Edelweiss's%20Radhika%20Gupta%20On%20Rohit%20Sharma%20Crying%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMillions%20of%20fans%20were%20left%20heartbroken%20and%20dejected%20after%20Team%20Australia%20beat%20India%20by%206%20wickets%20in%20the%20World%20Cup%20final.%20The%20Indian%20cricket%20team's%20dream%20of%20winning%20the%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%202023%20for%20the%20third%20time%20in%20its%20history%20ended%20on%20a%20sour%20note%2C%20as%20Australia%20secured%20a%20comfortable%20victory%20in%20the%20final%2C%20lifting%20the%20coveted%20trophy%20for%20the%206th%20time%20in%20their%20history.%20Several%20players%20also%20couldn't%20control%20their%20tears%20including%20Team%20India%20captain%20Rohit%20Sharma%20who%20made%20his%20way%20back%20to%20the%20dressing%20room%20with%20moist%20eyes.%20The%20picture%20has%20gone%20viral%2C%20evoking%20emotions%20on%20social%20media.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReacting%20to%20Mr%20Sharma's%20gut-wren